 style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">WHEN · HOW · travel exposure</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;background:#F8FAFC;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Direction · Purpose · Stay</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:13px;text-align:right;\">ENTRY · TRADE / commerce · sourcing goods · 14 days</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Journey start · Embarkation</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:13px;text-align:right;\">DR Congo · Goma</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Conveyance · Seat</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:13px;text-align:right;\">LAND BUS-KBZ-2314 · seat 14B</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Arrival · Departure</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;\">2026-04-21 12:30 → 2026-04-20 12:30</td></tr>\n  </table>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:10px;padding:10px 12px;background:#F8FAFC;border-left:3px solid #B91C1C;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;color:#475569;font-weight:700;\">Countries traversed</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:4px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>VISITED</strong> · DR Congo <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(2026-04-03 → 2026-04-19)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>TRANSIT</strong> · Rwanda <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(2026-04-19 → 2026-04-20)</span></li></ul></div>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">CLINICAL PICTURE</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;background:#F8FAFC;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Triage · General appearance</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:13px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">URGENT · UNWELL</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Emergency signs</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:13px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;color:#B91C1C;\">PRESENT</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Syndromic classification</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;\">VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Temperature</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;\">39.4 °C</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Pulse</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">112 bpm</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Respiratory rate</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;\">24 /min</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Blood pressure</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">98/60 mmHg</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">SpO₂</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">94 %</td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">SYMPTOMS · (8 recorded)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;\"><p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;font-size:13px;\">Symptoms PRESENT (6)</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 12px 18px;padding:0;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Bleeding gums or nose</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-21)</span> — Gums bled twice while brushing teeth</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Conjunctivitis</strong> — Bilateral scleral injection</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Continuous high-grade fever since arrival</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Retrosternal pain</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — Severe burning</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Severe fatigue</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Prostrate, unable to walk unassisted</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Very high fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — 39.4 °C at triage</li></ul><p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#047857;font-weight:600;font-size:13px;\">Explicitly ABSENT</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 4px 18px;padding:0;font-size:12px;\"><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Paralysis acute flaccid</li><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Rash vesicular pustular</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">KEY EXPOSURES</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#64748B;\">[UNKNOWN]</strong> Affected healthcare facility exposure — Visited local clinic in Goma for malaria test 5d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Close contact case — Relative died of haemorrhagic illness in Butembo 12d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Consumed bushmeat</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Contact with paralysis case</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Poultry or live bird exposure</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Travel from outbreak area — Returned from DRC North Kivu via Goma</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">WHY · Differential (4)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#1 · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 92% · 50.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Travel from North Kivu + haemorrhagic signs + contact with deceased case in Butembo</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#2 · Marburg Virus Disease (MVD)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 48% · 50.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Cannot exclude filovirus co-differential; fruit-bat exposure not confirmed</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#3 · Severe Malaria (P. falciparum)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 30% · 20.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">Endemic — CRITICAL</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Patient from DRC with fever — rule-out required before attributing bleeding to VHF</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#4 · Lassa fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 10% · 15.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">West-Africa travel absent but pharyngitis + retrosternal pain patterns similar</div></li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#FEF3C7;border-left:4px solid #B45309;border-radius:6px;margin:12px 0;\">\n  <tr><td style=\"padding:14px 16px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;color:#92400E;font-weight:700;\">Disease intelligence</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:17px;font-weight:700;color:#0F172A;margin:4px 0 2px;\">Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#475569;margin-bottom:10px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div>\n    <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\">\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;\">Case fatality rate</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">50.0%</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;\">Incubation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">2–21 days (typically 4–10)</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">Transmission</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Direct contact with body fluids of symptomatic case or contaminated fomites; sexual transmission from survivors; bat reservoir</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">PPE</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">VHF full PPE: fluid-resistant coverall, double gloves, PAPR or N95+face shield, hood, boots, apron</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">Isolation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Dedicated VHF isolation ward / treatment centre with buddy-system PPE donning/doffing</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">IHR notification</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">IMMEDIATE — any suspected VHF is a public health event of potential international concern</td></tr>\n    </table>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:10px;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>WHO case definition:</strong> Acute fever ≥38°C and ≥3 of: headache, vomiting, anorexia, diarrhoea, lethargy, abdominal pain, muscle/joint pain, difficulty swallowing, difficulty breathing, hiccup, OR unexplained bleeding, OR contact with suspected/confirmed case within 21 days.</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Differential:</strong> Marburg, Lassa, CCHF, severe malaria, typhoid, meningococcaemia, severe dengue</div>\n  </td></tr>\n</table></td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:0 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">Recommended tests · specimens</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Filovirus RT-PCR via BSL-4 reference lab (UVRI in Uganda)</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Rapid antigen test at case holding unit</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Malaria smear to rule in/out co-infection</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Liver function + coagulation (DIC picture)</li></ul>\n    <p style=\"margin:10px 0 0;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\"><strong>Specimens to collect:</strong> EDTA whole blood (5 mL), double-bagged, cold chain, dangerous-goods courier</p>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">Bedside red flags</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Travel from EVD-affected area within 21 days</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Contact with confirmed case, body fluids, or funeral</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Haemorrhagic signs in a febrile traveller</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Conjunctival injection + retrosternal pain typical early</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Rapid progression to shock / multi-organ failure</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">Samples collected (3)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">WHOLE_BLOOD_EDTA · ID: UVRI-183022-01 · → Uganda Virus Research Institute (UVRI), Entebbe · 2026-04-21 16:30:22</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">SERUM · ID: UVRI-183022-02 · → UVRI BSL-4 lab · 2026-04-21 16:30:22</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">ORAL_SWAB · ID: UVRI-183022-03 · → UVRI · 2026-04-21 16:30:22</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">Officer disposition + notes</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;font-size:13px;\"><strong>Disposition:</strong> ISOLATED <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(Transferred to Mulago VHF isolation ward under ambulance escort with full PPE team)</span></p>\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;font-size:13px;\"><strong>Outcome:</strong> SUSPECT_CASE · follow-up required: YES → NATIONAL</p>\n    <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\"><em>Patient febrile with scleral injection and retrosternal pain. Reports contact with relative who died of unspecified haemorrhagic illness in Butembo 12 days ago. Isolated on arrival per VHF protocol. IV fluids in situ. Samples double-bagged pending UVRI courier. Recommend immediate ring-investigation of bus cohort (seats 13-15).</em></p>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">Required follow-ups (14 · 1 overdue)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#0369A1;\">[IN_PROGRESS]</strong> Case investigation started <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 13:30:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Index case isolated / treatment initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 22:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Close contacts identified and listed <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Contact tracing and follow-up operational <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Coordination structure activated (EOC / PHEOC) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> WHO and partners notified per IHR Article 6 <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory specimens collected and transported <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory confirmation obtained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Epidemiological line list maintained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Risk communication to the public initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Infection prevention &amp; control (IPC) in facilities <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Vector control measures (if applicable) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Cross-border / POE surveillance strengthened <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Response resources mobilised <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">Context · prior alerts at MUTUKULA (last 30 days)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;\"><p style=\"margin:0;color:#64748B;font-size:13px;\">No other alerts at this POE in the past 30 days.</p></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:20px 28px 14px;\">\n  <div style=\"background:#B91C1C;border-radius:8px;padding:14px 16px;text-align:center;\">\n    <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#FFFFFF;font-size:14px;font-weight:700;text-decoration:none;\">Open DEMO_183022 in POE Sentinel console →</a>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:18px 28px 12px;background:#F1F5F9;border-top:1px solid #E2E8F0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:11px;color:#475569;line-height:1.5;\">\n    <strong>Uganda POE Sentinel</strong> · CRITICAL ALERT · WHO IHR 2005 &amp; AFRO IDSR 3rd Ed. aligned.<br>\n    Alert <strong>DEMO_183022</strong> · CRITICAL — life-threatening · fired 30 minutes ago at 2026-04-21 18:00.<br>\n    Open in console → <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#1D4ED8;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;\">http://localhost/#/active-alerts</a>\n  </p>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:8px 28px 18px;background:#F1F5F9;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:10px;color:#64748B;line-height:1.4;\">\n    This is a transactional public-health alert generated by the national surveillance pipeline. Do not reply; coordinate through the escalation ladder.<br>\n    Generated 2026-04-21 18:30 UTC · template DEMO_183022 · recipient action expected within 4h.\n  </p>\n</td></tr></table></td></tr></table></body></html>', 'ALERT', 21, 'UG', 'KYOTERA', 'MUTUKULA', 'SENT', NULL, 0, '2026-04-21 18:30:30', NULL, NULL, 'CMD:demo-all', '2026-04-21 18:30:30', '2026-04-21 18:30:30');
INSERT INTO `notification_log` (`id`, `contact_id`, `to_email`, `to_phone`, `channel`, `template_code`, `subject`, `body_preview`, `body_full`, `related_entity_type`, `related_entity_id`, `country_code`, `district_code`, `poe_code`, `status`, `error_message`, `retry_count`, `sent_at`, `delivered_at`, `failed_at`, `triggered_by`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(227, 119, 'ecsahccloudsurveillancealerts@gmail.com', NULL, 'EMAIL', 'ALERT_CRITICAL', '⛔ CRITICAL · DEMO_183022 · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · POE MUTUKULA · act within 4h', '\n  Uganda · POE SENTINEL · IHR 2005\n  CRITICAL PUBLIC HEALTH ALERT · acknowledge within 4 hours\n  ⛔ Suspected VHF — returned traveller from DRC North Kivu\n  [CRITICAL] · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · POE MUTUKULA · Uganda · FEMALE · 34 y · syndrome: VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER · CFR 50.0%\n  \n    Acknowledge by\n    2026-04-21 22:00 (4h SLA)\n    Escalation path: NATIONAL → WHO IHR NFP\n  \n\n\n\n  This alert was raised because a patient at the named Point of Entry meets CRITICAL surveillance criteria under ', '<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><meta charset=\"utf-8\"><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\"></head><body style=\"margin:0;padding:0;background:#EEF2F7;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;color:#0F172A;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#EEF2F7;padding:24px 12px;\"><tr><td align=\"center\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"640\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"max-width:640px;background:#FFFFFF;border-radius:10px;overflow:hidden;box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><tr><td style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,#7F1D1D 0%,#B91C1C 60%,#DC2626 100%);padding:24px 28px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#FECACA;font-weight:700;\">Uganda · POE SENTINEL · IHR 2005</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#FECACA;font-weight:600;\">CRITICAL PUBLIC HEALTH ALERT · acknowledge within 4 hours</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:10px;font-size:26px;font-weight:800;color:#FFFFFF;line-height:1.15;\">⛔ Suspected VHF — returned traveller from DRC North Kivu</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:14px;color:#FECACA;\">[CRITICAL] · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · POE MUTUKULA · Uganda · FEMALE · 34 y · syndrome: VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER · CFR 50.0%</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:14px;background:rgba(0,0,0,0.28);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.2);border-radius:6px;padding:10px 14px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;color:#FFFFFF;opacity:0.9;\">Acknowledge by</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:15px;color:#FFFFFF;font-weight:700;margin-top:2px;\">2026-04-21 22:00 (4h SLA)</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#FECACA;margin-top:4px;\">Escalation path: NATIONAL → WHO IHR NFP</div>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:22px 28px 6px;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">This alert was raised because a patient at the named Point of Entry meets CRITICAL surveillance criteria under IHR 2005 and national IDSR guidance. Full case dossier, disease intelligence, and the exact actions expected of you follow below.</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:18px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">WHAT · WHERE · WHO</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #FEE2E2;border-radius:8px;background:#FEF2F2;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #FEE2E2;font-size:12px;color:#7F1D1D;\">Alert code</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #FEE2E2;font-size:13px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;color:#7F1D1D;\">DEMO_183022</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #FEE2E2;font-size:12px;color:#7F1D1D;\">Risk classification</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #FEE2E2;font-size:13px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;color:#B91C1C;\">CRITICAL — life-threatening</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #FEE2E2;font-size:12px;color:#7F1D1D;\">Point of Entry · District</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #FEE2E2;font-size:13px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">MUTUKULA · KYOTERA</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #FEE2E2;font-size:12px;color:#7F1D1D;\">Country · Province</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #FEE2E2;font-size:13px;text-align:right;\">Uganda · CENTRAL</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #FEE2E2;font-size:12px;color:#7F1D1D;\">Detected by</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #FEE2E2;font-size:13px;text-align:right;\">Ayebare Timothy → case opened by Ayebare Timothy</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #FEE2E2;font-size:12px;color:#7F1D1D;\">Detected at · Case opened</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #FEE2E2;font-size:13px;text-align:right;\">2026-04-21 18:30 · 2026-04-21 13:30</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#7F1D1D;\">Alert status</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">OPEN</td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:18px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#7F1D1D;font-weight:800;\">ACT RIGHT NOW · CRITICAL</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:6px;padding:12px 14px;background:#FFFFFF;border:2px solid #B91C1C;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">IMMEDIATE VHF isolation — dedicated ETU or holding isolation</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Full VHF PPE for ALL contacts (including ambulance transfer)</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">IMMEDIATE WHO IHR + AFRO notification within 24h</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Ring-vaccinate contacts with rVSV-ZEBOV if EBOV confirmed</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Line-list contacts × 21 days; safe dignified burial if deceased</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Activate national Ebola response plan</li></ul>\n    <p style=\"margin:10px 0 0;font-size:12px;color:#7F1D1D;font-style:italic;\">⚠ These actions are time-critical. Any delay breaches the IHR 2005 notification window and the national 7-1-7 response target.</p>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:18px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">WHO · traveller profile</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;background:#F8FAFC;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Name · Age · Gender</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:13px;text-align:right;\"><strong>A. O.</strong> · 34 y · FEMALE</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Nationality · Occupation</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:13px;text-align:right;\">Uganda · Cross-border trader / market vendor</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Residence</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:13px;text-align:right;\">Uganda</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Reach · Emergency contact</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:13px;text-align:right;\">+25••••••••19 / a***@example.org · Robert Okello (spouse) / +256751000111</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Destination in country</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;\">KAMPALA — Mulago National Referral Hospital, Kampala</td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">WHEN · HOW · travel exposure</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;background:#F8FAFC;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Direction · Purpose · Stay</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:13px;text-align:right;\">ENTRY · TRADE / commerce · sourcing goods · 14 days</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Journey start · Embarkation</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:13px;text-align:right;\">DR Congo · Goma</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Conveyance · Seat</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:13px;text-align:right;\">LAND BUS-KBZ-2314 · seat 14B</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Arrival · Departure</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;\">2026-04-21 12:30 → 2026-04-20 12:30</td></tr>\n  </table>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:10px;padding:10px 12px;background:#F8FAFC;border-left:3px solid #B91C1C;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;color:#475569;font-weight:700;\">Countries traversed</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:4px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>VISITED</strong> · DR Congo <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(2026-04-03 → 2026-04-19)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>TRANSIT</strong> · Rwanda <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(2026-04-19 → 2026-04-20)</span></li></ul></div>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">CLINICAL PICTURE</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;background:#F8FAFC;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Triage · General appearance</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:13px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">URGENT · UNWELL</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Emergency signs</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E8F0;font-size:13px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;color:#B91C1C;\">PRESENT</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Syndromic classification</td><td style=\"padding:8px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;\">VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Temperature</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;\">39.4 °C</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Pulse</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">112 bpm</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Respiratory rate</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;\">24 /min</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Blood pressure</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">98/60 mmHg</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">SpO₂</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">94 %</td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">SYMPTOMS · (8 recorded)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;\"><p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;font-size:13px;\">Symptoms PRESENT (6)</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 12px 18px;padding:0;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Bleeding gums or nose</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-21)</span> — Gums bled twice while brushing teeth</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Conjunctivitis</strong> — Bilateral scleral injection</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Continuous high-grade fever since arrival</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Retrosternal pain</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — Severe burning</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Severe fatigue</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Prostrate, unable to walk unassisted</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Very high fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — 39.4 °C at triage</li></ul><p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#047857;font-weight:600;font-size:13px;\">Explicitly ABSENT</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 4px 18px;padding:0;font-size:12px;\"><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Paralysis acute flaccid</li><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Rash vesicular pustular</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">KEY EXPOSURES</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#64748B;\">[UNKNOWN]</strong> Affected healthcare facility exposure — Visited local clinic in Goma for malaria test 5d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Close contact case — Relative died of haemorrhagic illness in Butembo 12d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Consumed bushmeat</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Contact with paralysis case</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Poultry or live bird exposure</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Travel from outbreak area — Returned from DRC North Kivu via Goma</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">WHY · Differential (4)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#1 · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 92% · 50.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Travel from North Kivu + haemorrhagic signs + contact with deceased case in Butembo</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#2 · Marburg Virus Disease (MVD)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 48% · 50.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Cannot exclude filovirus co-differential; fruit-bat exposure not confirmed</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#3 · Severe Malaria (P. falciparum)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 30% · 20.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">Endemic — CRITICAL</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Patient from DRC with fever — rule-out required before attributing bleeding to VHF</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#4 · Lassa fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 10% · 15.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">West-Africa travel absent but pharyngitis + retrosternal pain patterns similar</div></li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#FEF3C7;border-left:4px solid #B45309;border-radius:6px;margin:12px 0;\">\n  <tr><td style=\"padding:14px 16px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;color:#92400E;font-weight:700;\">Disease intelligence</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:17px;font-weight:700;color:#0F172A;margin:4px 0 2px;\">Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#475569;margin-bottom:10px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div>\n    <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\">\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;\">Case fatality rate</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">50.0%</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;\">Incubation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">2–21 days (typically 4–10)</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">Transmission</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Direct contact with body fluids of symptomatic case or contaminated fomites; sexual transmission from survivors; bat reservoir</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">PPE</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">VHF full PPE: fluid-resistant coverall, double gloves, PAPR or N95+face shield, hood, boots, apron</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">Isolation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Dedicated VHF isolation ward / treatment centre with buddy-system PPE donning/doffing</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">IHR notification</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">IMMEDIATE — any suspected VHF is a public health event of potential international concern</td></tr>\n    </table>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:10px;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>WHO case definition:</strong> Acute fever ≥38°C and ≥3 of: headache, vomiting, anorexia, diarrhoea, lethargy, abdominal pain, muscle/joint pain, difficulty swallowing, difficulty breathing, hiccup, OR unexplained bleeding, OR contact with suspected/confirmed case within 21 days.</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Differential:</strong> Marburg, Lassa, CCHF, severe malaria, typhoid, meningococcaemia, severe dengue</div>\n  </td></tr>\n</table></td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:0 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">Recommended tests · specimens</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Filovirus RT-PCR via BSL-4 reference lab (UVRI in Uganda)</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Rapid antigen test at case holding unit</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Malaria smear to rule in/out co-infection</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Liver function + coagulation (DIC picture)</li></ul>\n    <p style=\"margin:10px 0 0;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\"><strong>Specimens to collect:</strong> EDTA whole blood (5 mL), double-bagged, cold chain, dangerous-goods courier</p>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">Bedside red flags</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Travel from EVD-affected area within 21 days</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Contact with confirmed case, body fluids, or funeral</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Haemorrhagic signs in a febrile traveller</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Conjunctival injection + retrosternal pain typical early</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Rapid progression to shock / multi-organ failure</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">Samples collected (3)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">WHOLE_BLOOD_EDTA · ID: UVRI-183022-01 · → Uganda Virus Research Institute (UVRI), Entebbe · 2026-04-21 16:30:22</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">SERUM · ID: UVRI-183022-02 · → UVRI BSL-4 lab · 2026-04-21 16:30:22</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">ORAL_SWAB · ID: UVRI-183022-03 · → UVRI · 2026-04-21 16:30:22</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">Officer disposition + notes</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;font-size:13px;\"><strong>Disposition:</strong> ISOLATED <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(Transferred to Mulago VHF isolation ward under ambulance escort with full PPE team)</span></p>\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;font-size:13px;\"><strong>Outcome:</strong> SUSPECT_CASE · follow-up required: YES → NATIONAL</p>\n    <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\"><em>Patient febrile with scleral injection and retrosternal pain. Reports contact with relative who died of unspecified haemorrhagic illness in Butembo 12 days ago. Isolated on arrival per VHF protocol. IV fluids in situ. Samples double-bagged pending UVRI courier. Recommend immediate ring-investigation of bus cohort (seats 13-15).</em></p>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">Required follow-ups (14 · 1 overdue)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#0369A1;\">[IN_PROGRESS]</strong> Case investigation started <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 13:30:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Index case isolated / treatment initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 22:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Close contacts identified and listed <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Contact tracing and follow-up operational <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Coordination structure activated (EOC / PHEOC) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> WHO and partners notified per IHR Article 6 <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory specimens collected and transported <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory confirmation obtained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Epidemiological line list maintained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Risk communication to the public initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Infection prevention &amp; control (IPC) in facilities <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Vector control measures (if applicable) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Cross-border / POE surveillance strengthened <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Response resources mobilised <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">Context · prior alerts at MUTUKULA (last 30 days)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;\"><p style=\"margin:0;color:#64748B;font-size:13px;\">No other alerts at this POE in the past 30 days.</p></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:20px 28px 14px;\">\n  <div style=\"background:#B91C1C;border-radius:8px;padding:14px 16px;text-align:center;\">\n    <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#FFFFFF;font-size:14px;font-weight:700;text-decoration:none;\">Open DEMO_183022 in POE Sentinel console →</a>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:18px 28px 12px;background:#F1F5F9;border-top:1px solid #E2E8F0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:11px;color:#475569;line-height:1.5;\">\n    <strong>Uganda POE Sentinel</strong> · CRITICAL ALERT · WHO IHR 2005 &amp; AFRO IDSR 3rd Ed. aligned.<br>\n    Alert <strong>DEMO_183022</strong> · CRITICAL — life-threatening · fired 30 minutes ago at 2026-04-21 18:00.<br>\n    Open in console → <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#1D4ED8;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;\">http://localhost/#/active-alerts</a>\n  </p>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:8px 28px 18px;background:#F1F5F9;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:10px;color:#64748B;line-height:1.4;\">\n    This is a transactional public-health alert generated by the national surveillance pipeline. Do not reply; coordinate through the escalation ladder.<br>\n    Generated 2026-04-21 18:30 UTC · template DEMO_183022 · recipient action expected within 4h.\n  </p>\n</td></tr></table></td></tr></table></body></html>', 'ALERT', 21, 'UG', 'KYOTERA', 'MUTUKULA', 'SENT', NULL, 0, '2026-04-21 18:30:31', NULL, NULL, 'CMD:demo-all', '2026-04-21 18:30:31', '2026-04-21 18:30:31');
INSERT INTO `notification_log` (`id`, `contact_id`, `to_email`, `to_phone`, `channel`, `template_code`, `subject`, `body_preview`, `body_full`, `related_entity_type`, `related_entity_id`, `country_code`, `district_code`, `poe_code`, `status`, `error_message`, `retry_count`, `sent_at`, `delivered_at`, `failed_at`, `triggered_by`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(228, 118, 'vexa256@gmail.com', NULL, 'EMAIL', 'ALERT_HIGH', '⚠ HIGH · DEMO_183022 · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · POE MUTUKULA', '\n  Uganda · POE SENTINEL · IHR 2005\n  HIGH-risk public health alert · acknowledge within 4 hours\n  ⚠ Suspected VHF — returned traveller from DRC North Kivu\n  [CRITICAL] · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · POE MUTUKULA · Uganda · FEMALE · 34 y · syndrome: VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER · CFR 50.0%\n\n\n\n  A HIGH-risk public-health event has been flagged at MUTUKULA. Review the case dossier, confirm disposition, and escalate to NATIONAL per the national ladder. Acknowledge in the console within 4 hours to mainta', '<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><meta charset=\"utf-8\"><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\"></head><body style=\"margin:0;padding:0;background:#EEF2F7;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;color:#0F172A;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#EEF2F7;padding:24px 12px;\"><tr><td align=\"center\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"640\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"max-width:640px;background:#FFFFFF;border-radius:10px;overflow:hidden;box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><tr><td style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,#92400E 0%,#D97706 60%,#F59E0B 100%);padding:24px 28px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#FEF3C7;font-weight:700;\">Uganda · POE SENTINEL · IHR 2005</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#FEF3C7;font-weight:600;\">HIGH-risk public health alert · acknowledge within 4 hours</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:10px;font-size:24px;font-weight:800;color:#FFFFFF;line-height:1.15;\">⚠ Suspected VHF — returned traveller from DRC North Kivu</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:14px;color:#FEF3C7;\">[CRITICAL] · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · POE MUTUKULA · Uganda · FEMALE · 34 y · syndrome: VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER · CFR 50.0%</div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:20px 28px 4px;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">A HIGH-risk public-health event has been flagged at MUTUKULA. Review the case dossier, confirm disposition, and escalate to NATIONAL per the national ladder. Acknowledge in the console within 4 hours to maintain the 7-1-7 response window.</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"background:#FEF3C7;border:1px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:8px;padding:12px 14px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Situation at a glance</div>\n    <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;font-size:12px;\">\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#78350F;\">Alert</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">DEMO_183022</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#78350F;\">Risk</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;color:#B45309;\">CRITICAL — life-threatening</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#78350F;\">Location</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">POE MUTUKULA · KYOTERA · Uganda</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#78350F;\">Detected by</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Ayebare Timothy at 2026-04-21 18:30</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#78350F;\">Case opened by</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Ayebare Timothy at 2026-04-21 13:30</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#78350F;\">Acknowledge by</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">2026-04-21 22:00</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#78350F;\">Ladder</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">NATIONAL → WHO IHR NFP</td></tr>\n    </table>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:18px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Traveller profile</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;font-size:12px;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:4px 0;color:#475569;\">Identity</td><td style=\"padding:4px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">A. O. · 34 y · FEMALE</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:4px 0;color:#475569;\">Nationality · Residence</td><td style=\"padding:4px 0;text-align:right;\">Uganda · Uganda</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:4px 0;color:#475569;\">Occupation</td><td style=\"padding:4px 0;text-align:right;\">Cross-border trader / market vendor</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:4px 0;color:#475569;\">Destination</td><td style=\"padding:4px 0;text-align:right;\">KAMPALA · Mulago National Referral Hospital, Kampala</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:4px 0;color:#475569;\">Reach</td><td style=\"padding:4px 0;text-align:right;\">+25••••••••19 · a***@example.org</td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Travel history</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:10px 14px;background:#FFFBEB;border:1px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;font-size:12px;color:#78350F;\">ENTRY · LAND BUS-KBZ-2314 · seat 14B · arrival 2026-04-21 12:30</p>\n    <ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>VISITED</strong> · DR Congo <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(2026-04-03 → 2026-04-19)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>TRANSIT</strong> · Rwanda <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(2026-04-19 → 2026-04-20)</span></li></ul>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Clinical picture</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;background:#FFFBEB;border:1px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#78350F;\">Triage · general appearance</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">URGENT · UNWELL</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#78350F;\">Emergency signs</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;color:#B45309;\">PRESENT</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#78350F;\">Syndrome</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Temperature</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;\">39.4 °C</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Pulse</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">112 bpm</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Respiratory rate</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;\">24 /min</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Blood pressure</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">98/60 mmHg</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">SpO₂</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">94 %</td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Symptoms (8) &amp; exposures</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#FFFBEB;border:1px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;font-size:13px;\">Symptoms PRESENT (6)</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 12px 18px;padding:0;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Bleeding gums or nose</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-21)</span> — Gums bled twice while brushing teeth</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Conjunctivitis</strong> — Bilateral scleral injection</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Continuous high-grade fever since arrival</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Retrosternal pain</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — Severe burning</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Severe fatigue</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Prostrate, unable to walk unassisted</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Very high fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — 39.4 °C at triage</li></ul><p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#047857;font-weight:600;font-size:13px;\">Explicitly ABSENT</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 4px 18px;padding:0;font-size:12px;\"><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Paralysis acute flaccid</li><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Rash vesicular pustular</li></ul>\n    <hr style=\"border:none;border-top:1px dashed #FCD34D;margin:10px 0;\">\n    <ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#64748B;\">[UNKNOWN]</strong> Affected healthcare facility exposure — Visited local clinic in Goma for malaria test 5d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Close contact case — Relative died of haemorrhagic illness in Butembo 12d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Consumed bushmeat</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Contact with paralysis case</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Poultry or live bird exposure</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Travel from outbreak area — Returned from DRC North Kivu via Goma</li></ul>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Differential (4)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#FFFBEB;border:1px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:8px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#1 · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 92% · 50.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Travel from North Kivu + haemorrhagic signs + contact with deceased case in Butembo</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#2 · Marburg Virus Disease (MVD)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 48% · 50.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Cannot exclude filovirus co-differential; fruit-bat exposure not confirmed</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#3 · Severe Malaria (P. falciparum)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 30% · 20.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">Endemic — CRITICAL</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Patient from DRC with fever — rule-out required before attributing bleeding to VHF</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#4 · Lassa fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 10% · 15.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">West-Africa travel absent but pharyngitis + retrosternal pain patterns similar</div></li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#FEF3C7;border-left:4px solid #B45309;border-radius:6px;margin:12px 0;\">\n  <tr><td style=\"padding:14px 16px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;color:#92400E;font-weight:700;\">Disease intelligence</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:17px;font-weight:700;color:#0F172A;margin:4px 0 2px;\">Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#475569;margin-bottom:10px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div>\n    <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\">\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;\">Case fatality rate</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">50.0%</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;\">Incubation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">2–21 days (typically 4–10)</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">Transmission</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Direct contact with body fluids of symptomatic case or contaminated fomites; sexual transmission from survivors; bat reservoir</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">PPE</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">VHF full PPE: fluid-resistant coverall, double gloves, PAPR or N95+face shield, hood, boots, apron</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">Isolation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Dedicated VHF isolation ward / treatment centre with buddy-system PPE donning/doffing</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">IHR notification</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">IMMEDIATE — any suspected VHF is a public health event of potential international concern</td></tr>\n    </table>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:10px;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>WHO case definition:</strong> Acute fever ≥38°C and ≥3 of: headache, vomiting, anorexia, diarrhoea, lethargy, abdominal pain, muscle/joint pain, difficulty swallowing, difficulty breathing, hiccup, OR unexplained bleeding, OR contact with suspected/confirmed case within 21 days.</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Differential:</strong> Marburg, Lassa, CCHF, severe malaria, typhoid, meningococcaemia, severe dengue</div>\n  </td></tr>\n</table></td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:0 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Immediate actions</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#FFFFFF;border:2px solid #F59E0B;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">IMMEDIATE VHF isolation — dedicated ETU or holding isolation</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Full VHF PPE for ALL contacts (including ambulance transfer)</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">IMMEDIATE WHO IHR + AFRO notification within 24h</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Ring-vaccinate contacts with rVSV-ZEBOV if EBOV confirmed</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Line-list contacts × 21 days; safe dignified burial if deceased</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Activate national Ebola response plan</li></ul>\n    <p style=\"margin:10px 0 0;font-size:12px;color:#92400E;\">Recommended tests: see below. Collect specimens per disease protocol: <strong>EDTA whole blood (5 mL), double-bagged, cold chain, dangerous-goods courier</strong>.</p>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Recommended tests</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#FFFBEB;border:1px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:8px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Filovirus RT-PCR via BSL-4 reference lab (UVRI in Uganda)</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Rapid antigen test at case holding unit</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Malaria smear to rule in/out co-infection</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Liver function + coagulation (DIC picture)</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Samples &amp; follow-ups</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#FFFBEB;border:1px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;font-size:12px;color:#78350F;\"><strong>Samples recorded (3)</strong></p>\n    <ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">WHOLE_BLOOD_EDTA · ID: UVRI-183022-01 · → Uganda Virus Research Institute (UVRI), Entebbe · 2026-04-21 16:30:22</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">SERUM · ID: UVRI-183022-02 · → UVRI BSL-4 lab · 2026-04-21 16:30:22</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">ORAL_SWAB · ID: UVRI-183022-03 · → UVRI · 2026-04-21 16:30:22</li></ul>\n    <hr style=\"border:none;border-top:1px dashed #FCD34D;margin:10px 0;\">\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;font-size:12px;color:#78350F;\"><strong>Follow-up actions (14 seeded · 1 overdue)</strong></p>\n    <ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#0369A1;\">[IN_PROGRESS]</strong> Case investigation started <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 13:30:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Index case isolated / treatment initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 22:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Close contacts identified and listed <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Contact tracing and follow-up operational <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Coordination structure activated (EOC / PHEOC) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> WHO and partners notified per IHR Article 6 <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory specimens collected and transported <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory confirmation obtained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Epidemiological line list maintained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Risk communication to the public initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Infection prevention &amp; control (IPC) in facilities <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Vector control measures (if applicable) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Cross-border / POE surveillance strengthened <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Response resources mobilised <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li></ul>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Context · prior alerts at MUTUKULA</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#FFFBEB;border:1px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:8px;\"><p style=\"margin:0;color:#64748B;font-size:13px;\">No other alerts at this POE in the past 30 days.</p></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:20px 28px 14px;\">\n  <div style=\"background:#D97706;border-radius:8px;padding:14px 16px;text-align:center;\">\n    <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#FFFFFF;font-size:14px;font-weight:700;text-decoration:none;\">Open DEMO_183022 in POE Sentinel →</a>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:18px 28px 12px;background:#F1F5F9;border-top:1px solid #E2E8F0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:11px;color:#475569;line-height:1.5;\">\n    <strong>Uganda POE Sentinel</strong> · HIGH-RISK ALERT · WHO IHR 2005 &amp; AFRO IDSR 3rd Ed. aligned.<br>\n    Alert <strong>DEMO_183022</strong> · CRITICAL — life-threatening · fired 30 minutes ago at 2026-04-21 18:00.<br>\n    Open in console → <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#1D4ED8;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;\">http://localhost/#/active-alerts</a>\n  </p>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:8px 28px 18px;background:#F1F5F9;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:10px;color:#64748B;line-height:1.4;\">\n    This is a transactional public-health alert generated by the national surveillance pipeline. Do not reply; coordinate through the escalation ladder.<br>\n    Generated 2026-04-21 18:30 UTC · template DEMO_183022 · recipient action expected within 4h.\n  </p>\n</td></tr></table></td></tr></table></body></html>', 'ALERT', 21, 'UG', 'KYOTERA', 'MUTUKULA', 'SENT', NULL, 0, '2026-04-21 18:30:33', NULL, NULL, 'CMD:demo-all', '2026-04-21 18:30:33', '2026-04-21 18:30:33'),
(229, 54, 'ayebare.k.timothy@gmail.com', NULL, 'EMAIL', 'ALERT_HIGH', '⚠ HIGH · DEMO_183022 · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · POE MUTUKULA', '\n  Uganda · POE SENTINEL · IHR 2005\n  HIGH-risk public health alert · acknowledge within 4 hours\n  ⚠ Suspected VHF — returned traveller from DRC North Kivu\n  [CRITICAL] · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · POE MUTUKULA · Uganda · FEMALE · 34 y · syndrome: VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER · CFR 50.0%\n\n\n\n  A HIGH-risk public-health event has been flagged at MUTUKULA. Review the case dossier, confirm disposition, and escalate to NATIONAL per the national ladder. Acknowledge in the console within 4 hours to mainta', '<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><meta charset=\"utf-8\"><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\"></head><body style=\"margin:0;padding:0;background:#EEF2F7;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;color:#0F172A;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#EEF2F7;padding:24px 12px;\"><tr><td align=\"center\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"640\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"max-width:640px;background:#FFFFFF;border-radius:10px;overflow:hidden;box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><tr><td style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,#92400E 0%,#D97706 60%,#F59E0B 100%);padding:24px 28px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#FEF3C7;font-weight:700;\">Uganda · POE SENTINEL · IHR 2005</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#FEF3C7;font-weight:600;\">HIGH-risk public health alert · acknowledge within 4 hours</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:10px;font-size:24px;font-weight:800;color:#FFFFFF;line-height:1.15;\">⚠ Suspected VHF — returned traveller from DRC North Kivu</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:14px;color:#FEF3C7;\">[CRITICAL] · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · POE MUTUKULA · Uganda · FEMALE · 34 y · syndrome: VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER · CFR 50.0%</div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:20px 28px 4px;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">A HIGH-risk public-health event has been flagged at MUTUKULA. Review the case dossier, confirm disposition, and escalate to NATIONAL per the national ladder. Acknowledge in the console within 4 hours to maintain the 7-1-7 response window.</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"background:#FEF3C7;border:1px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:8px;padding:12px 14px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Situation at a glance</div>\n    <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;font-size:12px;\">\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#78350F;\">Alert</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">DEMO_183022</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#78350F;\">Risk</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;color:#B45309;\">CRITICAL — life-threatening</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#78350F;\">Location</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">POE MUTUKULA · KYOTERA · Uganda</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#78350F;\">Detected by</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Ayebare Timothy at 2026-04-21 18:30</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#78350F;\">Case opened by</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Ayebare Timothy at 2026-04-21 13:30</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#78350F;\">Acknowledge by</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">2026-04-21 22:00</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#78350F;\">Ladder</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">NATIONAL → WHO IHR NFP</td></tr>\n    </table>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:18px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Traveller profile</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;font-size:12px;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:4px 0;color:#475569;\">Identity</td><td style=\"padding:4px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">A. O. · 34 y · FEMALE</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:4px 0;color:#475569;\">Nationality · Residence</td><td style=\"padding:4px 0;text-align:right;\">Uganda · Uganda</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:4px 0;color:#475569;\">Occupation</td><td style=\"padding:4px 0;text-align:right;\">Cross-border trader / market vendor</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:4px 0;color:#475569;\">Destination</td><td style=\"padding:4px 0;text-align:right;\">KAMPALA · Mulago National Referral Hospital, Kampala</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:4px 0;color:#475569;\">Reach</td><td style=\"padding:4px 0;text-align:right;\">+25••••••••19 · a***@example.org</td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Travel history</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:10px 14px;background:#FFFBEB;border:1px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;font-size:12px;color:#78350F;\">ENTRY · LAND BUS-KBZ-2314 · seat 14B · arrival 2026-04-21 12:30</p>\n    <ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>VISITED</strong> · DR Congo <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(2026-04-03 → 2026-04-19)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>TRANSIT</strong> · Rwanda <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(2026-04-19 → 2026-04-20)</span></li></ul>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Clinical picture</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;background:#FFFBEB;border:1px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#78350F;\">Triage · general appearance</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">URGENT · UNWELL</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#78350F;\">Emergency signs</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;color:#B45309;\">PRESENT</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#78350F;\">Syndrome</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Temperature</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;\">39.4 °C</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Pulse</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">112 bpm</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Respiratory rate</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;\">24 /min</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Blood pressure</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">98/60 mmHg</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">SpO₂</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">94 %</td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Symptoms (8) &amp; exposures</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#FFFBEB;border:1px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;font-size:13px;\">Symptoms PRESENT (6)</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 12px 18px;padding:0;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Bleeding gums or nose</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-21)</span> — Gums bled twice while brushing teeth</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Conjunctivitis</strong> — Bilateral scleral injection</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Continuous high-grade fever since arrival</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Retrosternal pain</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — Severe burning</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Severe fatigue</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Prostrate, unable to walk unassisted</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Very high fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — 39.4 °C at triage</li></ul><p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#047857;font-weight:600;font-size:13px;\">Explicitly ABSENT</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 4px 18px;padding:0;font-size:12px;\"><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Paralysis acute flaccid</li><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Rash vesicular pustular</li></ul>\n    <hr style=\"border:none;border-top:1px dashed #FCD34D;margin:10px 0;\">\n    <ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#64748B;\">[UNKNOWN]</strong> Affected healthcare facility exposure — Visited local clinic in Goma for malaria test 5d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Close contact case — Relative died of haemorrhagic illness in Butembo 12d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Consumed bushmeat</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Contact with paralysis case</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Poultry or live bird exposure</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Travel from outbreak area — Returned from DRC North Kivu via Goma</li></ul>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Differential (4)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#FFFBEB;border:1px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:8px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#1 · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 92% · 50.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Travel from North Kivu + haemorrhagic signs + contact with deceased case in Butembo</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#2 · Marburg Virus Disease (MVD)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 48% · 50.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Cannot exclude filovirus co-differential; fruit-bat exposure not confirmed</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#3 · Severe Malaria (P. falciparum)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 30% · 20.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">Endemic — CRITICAL</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Patient from DRC with fever — rule-out required before attributing bleeding to VHF</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#4 · Lassa fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 10% · 15.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">West-Africa travel absent but pharyngitis + retrosternal pain patterns similar</div></li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#FEF3C7;border-left:4px solid #B45309;border-radius:6px;margin:12px 0;\">\n  <tr><td style=\"padding:14px 16px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;color:#92400E;font-weight:700;\">Disease intelligence</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:17px;font-weight:700;color:#0F172A;margin:4px 0 2px;\">Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#475569;margin-bottom:10px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div>\n    <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\">\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;\">Case fatality rate</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">50.0%</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;\">Incubation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">2–21 days (typically 4–10)</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">Transmission</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Direct contact with body fluids of symptomatic case or contaminated fomites; sexual transmission from survivors; bat reservoir</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">PPE</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">VHF full PPE: fluid-resistant coverall, double gloves, PAPR or N95+face shield, hood, boots, apron</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">Isolation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Dedicated VHF isolation ward / treatment centre with buddy-system PPE donning/doffing</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">IHR notification</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">IMMEDIATE — any suspected VHF is a public health event of potential international concern</td></tr>\n    </table>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:10px;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>WHO case definition:</strong> Acute fever ≥38°C and ≥3 of: headache, vomiting, anorexia, diarrhoea, lethargy, abdominal pain, muscle/joint pain, difficulty swallowing, difficulty breathing, hiccup, OR unexplained bleeding, OR contact with suspected/confirmed case within 21 days.</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Differential:</strong> Marburg, Lassa, CCHF, severe malaria, typhoid, meningococcaemia, severe dengue</div>\n  </td></tr>\n</table></td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:0 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Immediate actions</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#FFFFFF;border:2px solid #F59E0B;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">IMMEDIATE VHF isolation — dedicated ETU or holding isolation</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Full VHF PPE for ALL contacts (including ambulance transfer)</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">IMMEDIATE WHO IHR + AFRO notification within 24h</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Ring-vaccinate contacts with rVSV-ZEBOV if EBOV confirmed</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Line-list contacts × 21 days; safe dignified burial if deceased</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Activate national Ebola response plan</li></ul>\n    <p style=\"margin:10px 0 0;font-size:12px;color:#92400E;\">Recommended tests: see below. Collect specimens per disease protocol: <strong>EDTA whole blood (5 mL), double-bagged, cold chain, dangerous-goods courier</strong>.</p>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Recommended tests</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#FFFBEB;border:1px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:8px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Filovirus RT-PCR via BSL-4 reference lab (UVRI in Uganda)</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Rapid antigen test at case holding unit</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Malaria smear to rule in/out co-infection</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Liver function + coagulation (DIC picture)</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Samples &amp; follow-ups</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#FFFBEB;border:1px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;font-size:12px;color:#78350F;\"><strong>Samples recorded (3)</strong></p>\n    <ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">WHOLE_BLOOD_EDTA · ID: UVRI-183022-01 · → Uganda Virus Research Institute (UVRI), Entebbe · 2026-04-21 16:30:22</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">SERUM · ID: UVRI-183022-02 · → UVRI BSL-4 lab · 2026-04-21 16:30:22</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">ORAL_SWAB · ID: UVRI-183022-03 · → UVRI · 2026-04-21 16:30:22</li></ul>\n    <hr style=\"border:none;border-top:1px dashed #FCD34D;margin:10px 0;\">\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;font-size:12px;color:#78350F;\"><strong>Follow-up actions (14 seeded · 1 overdue)</strong></p>\n    <ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#0369A1;\">[IN_PROGRESS]</strong> Case investigation started <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 13:30:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Index case isolated / treatment initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 22:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Close contacts identified and listed <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Contact tracing and follow-up operational <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Coordination structure activated (EOC / PHEOC) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> WHO and partners notified per IHR Article 6 <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory specimens collected and transported <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory confirmation obtained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Epidemiological line list maintained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Risk communication to the public initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Infection prevention &amp; control (IPC) in facilities <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Vector control measures (if applicable) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Cross-border / POE surveillance strengthened <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Response resources mobilised <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li></ul>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Context · prior alerts at MUTUKULA</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#FFFBEB;border:1px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:8px;\"><p style=\"margin:0;color:#64748B;font-size:13px;\">No other alerts at this POE in the past 30 days.</p></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:20px 28px 14px;\">\n  <div style=\"background:#D97706;border-radius:8px;padding:14px 16px;text-align:center;\">\n    <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#FFFFFF;font-size:14px;font-weight:700;text-decoration:none;\">Open DEMO_183022 in POE Sentinel →</a>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:18px 28px 12px;background:#F1F5F9;border-top:1px solid #E2E8F0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:11px;color:#475569;line-height:1.5;\">\n    <strong>Uganda POE Sentinel</strong> · HIGH-RISK ALERT · WHO IHR 2005 &amp; AFRO IDSR 3rd Ed. aligned.<br>\n    Alert <strong>DEMO_183022</strong> · CRITICAL — life-threatening · fired 30 minutes ago at 2026-04-21 18:00.<br>\n    Open in console → <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#1D4ED8;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;\">http://localhost/#/active-alerts</a>\n  </p>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:8px 28px 18px;background:#F1F5F9;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:10px;color:#64748B;line-height:1.4;\">\n    This is a transactional public-health alert generated by the national surveillance pipeline. Do not reply; coordinate through the escalation ladder.<br>\n    Generated 2026-04-21 18:30 UTC · template DEMO_183022 · recipient action expected within 4h.\n  </p>\n</td></tr></table></td></tr></table></body></html>', 'ALERT', 21, 'UG', 'KYOTERA', 'MUTUKULA', 'SENT', NULL, 0, '2026-04-21 18:30:35', NULL, NULL, 'CMD:demo-all', '2026-04-21 18:30:35', '2026-04-21 18:30:35');
INSERT INTO `notification_log` (`id`, `contact_id`, `to_email`, `to_phone`, `channel`, `template_code`, `subject`, `body_preview`, `body_full`, `related_entity_type`, `related_entity_id`, `country_code`, `district_code`, `poe_code`, `status`, `error_message`, `retry_count`, `sent_at`, `delivered_at`, `failed_at`, `triggered_by`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(230, 119, 'ecsahccloudsurveillancealerts@gmail.com', NULL, 'EMAIL', 'ALERT_HIGH', '⚠ HIGH · DEMO_183022 · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · POE MUTUKULA', '\n  Uganda · POE SENTINEL · IHR 2005\n  HIGH-risk public health alert · acknowledge within 4 hours\n  ⚠ Suspected VHF — returned traveller from DRC North Kivu\n  [CRITICAL] · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · POE MUTUKULA · Uganda · FEMALE · 34 y · syndrome: VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER · CFR 50.0%\n\n\n\n  A HIGH-risk public-health event has been flagged at MUTUKULA. Review the case dossier, confirm disposition, and escalate to NATIONAL per the national ladder. Acknowledge in the console within 4 hours to mainta', '<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><meta charset=\"utf-8\"><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\"></head><body style=\"margin:0;padding:0;background:#EEF2F7;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;color:#0F172A;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#EEF2F7;padding:24px 12px;\"><tr><td align=\"center\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"640\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"max-width:640px;background:#FFFFFF;border-radius:10px;overflow:hidden;box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><tr><td style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,#92400E 0%,#D97706 60%,#F59E0B 100%);padding:24px 28px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#FEF3C7;font-weight:700;\">Uganda · POE SENTINEL · IHR 2005</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#FEF3C7;font-weight:600;\">HIGH-risk public health alert · acknowledge within 4 hours</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:10px;font-size:24px;font-weight:800;color:#FFFFFF;line-height:1.15;\">⚠ Suspected VHF — returned traveller from DRC North Kivu</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:14px;color:#FEF3C7;\">[CRITICAL] · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · POE MUTUKULA · Uganda · FEMALE · 34 y · syndrome: VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER · CFR 50.0%</div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:20px 28px 4px;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">A HIGH-risk public-health event has been flagged at MUTUKULA. Review the case dossier, confirm disposition, and escalate to NATIONAL per the national ladder. Acknowledge in the console within 4 hours to maintain the 7-1-7 response window.</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"background:#FEF3C7;border:1px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:8px;padding:12px 14px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Situation at a glance</div>\n    <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;font-size:12px;\">\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#78350F;\">Alert</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">DEMO_183022</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#78350F;\">Risk</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;color:#B45309;\">CRITICAL — life-threatening</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#78350F;\">Location</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">POE MUTUKULA · KYOTERA · Uganda</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#78350F;\">Detected by</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Ayebare Timothy at 2026-04-21 18:30</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#78350F;\">Case opened by</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Ayebare Timothy at 2026-04-21 13:30</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#78350F;\">Acknowledge by</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">2026-04-21 22:00</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#78350F;\">Ladder</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">NATIONAL → WHO IHR NFP</td></tr>\n    </table>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:18px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Traveller profile</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;font-size:12px;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:4px 0;color:#475569;\">Identity</td><td style=\"padding:4px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">A. O. · 34 y · FEMALE</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:4px 0;color:#475569;\">Nationality · Residence</td><td style=\"padding:4px 0;text-align:right;\">Uganda · Uganda</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:4px 0;color:#475569;\">Occupation</td><td style=\"padding:4px 0;text-align:right;\">Cross-border trader / market vendor</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:4px 0;color:#475569;\">Destination</td><td style=\"padding:4px 0;text-align:right;\">KAMPALA · Mulago National Referral Hospital, Kampala</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:4px 0;color:#475569;\">Reach</td><td style=\"padding:4px 0;text-align:right;\">+25••••••••19 · a***@example.org</td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Travel history</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:10px 14px;background:#FFFBEB;border:1px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;font-size:12px;color:#78350F;\">ENTRY · LAND BUS-KBZ-2314 · seat 14B · arrival 2026-04-21 12:30</p>\n    <ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>VISITED</strong> · DR Congo <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(2026-04-03 → 2026-04-19)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>TRANSIT</strong> · Rwanda <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(2026-04-19 → 2026-04-20)</span></li></ul>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Clinical picture</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;background:#FFFBEB;border:1px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#78350F;\">Triage · general appearance</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">URGENT · UNWELL</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#78350F;\">Emergency signs</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;color:#B45309;\">PRESENT</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#78350F;\">Syndrome</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Temperature</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;\">39.4 °C</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Pulse</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">112 bpm</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Respiratory rate</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;\">24 /min</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Blood pressure</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">98/60 mmHg</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">SpO₂</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">94 %</td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Symptoms (8) &amp; exposures</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#FFFBEB;border:1px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;font-size:13px;\">Symptoms PRESENT (6)</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 12px 18px;padding:0;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Bleeding gums or nose</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-21)</span> — Gums bled twice while brushing teeth</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Conjunctivitis</strong> — Bilateral scleral injection</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Continuous high-grade fever since arrival</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Retrosternal pain</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — Severe burning</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Severe fatigue</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Prostrate, unable to walk unassisted</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Very high fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — 39.4 °C at triage</li></ul><p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#047857;font-weight:600;font-size:13px;\">Explicitly ABSENT</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 4px 18px;padding:0;font-size:12px;\"><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Paralysis acute flaccid</li><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Rash vesicular pustular</li></ul>\n    <hr style=\"border:none;border-top:1px dashed #FCD34D;margin:10px 0;\">\n    <ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#64748B;\">[UNKNOWN]</strong> Affected healthcare facility exposure — Visited local clinic in Goma for malaria test 5d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Close contact case — Relative died of haemorrhagic illness in Butembo 12d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Consumed bushmeat</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Contact with paralysis case</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Poultry or live bird exposure</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Travel from outbreak area — Returned from DRC North Kivu via Goma</li></ul>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Differential (4)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#FFFBEB;border:1px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:8px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#1 · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 92% · 50.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Travel from North Kivu + haemorrhagic signs + contact with deceased case in Butembo</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#2 · Marburg Virus Disease (MVD)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 48% · 50.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Cannot exclude filovirus co-differential; fruit-bat exposure not confirmed</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#3 · Severe Malaria (P. falciparum)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 30% · 20.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">Endemic — CRITICAL</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Patient from DRC with fever — rule-out required before attributing bleeding to VHF</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#4 · Lassa fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 10% · 15.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">West-Africa travel absent but pharyngitis + retrosternal pain patterns similar</div></li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#FEF3C7;border-left:4px solid #B45309;border-radius:6px;margin:12px 0;\">\n  <tr><td style=\"padding:14px 16px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;color:#92400E;font-weight:700;\">Disease intelligence</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:17px;font-weight:700;color:#0F172A;margin:4px 0 2px;\">Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#475569;margin-bottom:10px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div>\n    <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\">\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;\">Case fatality rate</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">50.0%</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;\">Incubation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">2–21 days (typically 4–10)</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">Transmission</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Direct contact with body fluids of symptomatic case or contaminated fomites; sexual transmission from survivors; bat reservoir</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">PPE</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">VHF full PPE: fluid-resistant coverall, double gloves, PAPR or N95+face shield, hood, boots, apron</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">Isolation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Dedicated VHF isolation ward / treatment centre with buddy-system PPE donning/doffing</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">IHR notification</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">IMMEDIATE — any suspected VHF is a public health event of potential international concern</td></tr>\n    </table>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:10px;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>WHO case definition:</strong> Acute fever ≥38°C and ≥3 of: headache, vomiting, anorexia, diarrhoea, lethargy, abdominal pain, muscle/joint pain, difficulty swallowing, difficulty breathing, hiccup, OR unexplained bleeding, OR contact with suspected/confirmed case within 21 days.</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Differential:</strong> Marburg, Lassa, CCHF, severe malaria, typhoid, meningococcaemia, severe dengue</div>\n  </td></tr>\n</table></td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:0 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Immediate actions</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#FFFFFF;border:2px solid #F59E0B;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">IMMEDIATE VHF isolation — dedicated ETU or holding isolation</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Full VHF PPE for ALL contacts (including ambulance transfer)</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">IMMEDIATE WHO IHR + AFRO notification within 24h</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Ring-vaccinate contacts with rVSV-ZEBOV if EBOV confirmed</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Line-list contacts × 21 days; safe dignified burial if deceased</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Activate national Ebola response plan</li></ul>\n    <p style=\"margin:10px 0 0;font-size:12px;color:#92400E;\">Recommended tests: see below. Collect specimens per disease protocol: <strong>EDTA whole blood (5 mL), double-bagged, cold chain, dangerous-goods courier</strong>.</p>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Recommended tests</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#FFFBEB;border:1px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:8px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Filovirus RT-PCR via BSL-4 reference lab (UVRI in Uganda)</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Rapid antigen test at case holding unit</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Malaria smear to rule in/out co-infection</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Liver function + coagulation (DIC picture)</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Samples &amp; follow-ups</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#FFFBEB;border:1px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;font-size:12px;color:#78350F;\"><strong>Samples recorded (3)</strong></p>\n    <ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">WHOLE_BLOOD_EDTA · ID: UVRI-183022-01 · → Uganda Virus Research Institute (UVRI), Entebbe · 2026-04-21 16:30:22</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">SERUM · ID: UVRI-183022-02 · → UVRI BSL-4 lab · 2026-04-21 16:30:22</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">ORAL_SWAB · ID: UVRI-183022-03 · → UVRI · 2026-04-21 16:30:22</li></ul>\n    <hr style=\"border:none;border-top:1px dashed #FCD34D;margin:10px 0;\">\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;font-size:12px;color:#78350F;\"><strong>Follow-up actions (14 seeded · 1 overdue)</strong></p>\n    <ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#0369A1;\">[IN_PROGRESS]</strong> Case investigation started <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 13:30:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Index case isolated / treatment initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 22:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Close contacts identified and listed <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Contact tracing and follow-up operational <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Coordination structure activated (EOC / PHEOC) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> WHO and partners notified per IHR Article 6 <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory specimens collected and transported <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory confirmation obtained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Epidemiological line list maintained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Risk communication to the public initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Infection prevention &amp; control (IPC) in facilities <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Vector control measures (if applicable) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Cross-border / POE surveillance strengthened <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Response resources mobilised <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li></ul>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#92400E;font-weight:800;\">Context · prior alerts at MUTUKULA</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#FFFBEB;border:1px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:8px;\"><p style=\"margin:0;color:#64748B;font-size:13px;\">No other alerts at this POE in the past 30 days.</p></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:20px 28px 14px;\">\n  <div style=\"background:#D97706;border-radius:8px;padding:14px 16px;text-align:center;\">\n    <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#FFFFFF;font-size:14px;font-weight:700;text-decoration:none;\">Open DEMO_183022 in POE Sentinel →</a>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:18px 28px 12px;background:#F1F5F9;border-top:1px solid #E2E8F0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:11px;color:#475569;line-height:1.5;\">\n    <strong>Uganda POE Sentinel</strong> · HIGH-RISK ALERT · WHO IHR 2005 &amp; AFRO IDSR 3rd Ed. aligned.<br>\n    Alert <strong>DEMO_183022</strong> · CRITICAL — life-threatening · fired 30 minutes ago at 2026-04-21 18:00.<br>\n    Open in console → <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#1D4ED8;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;\">http://localhost/#/active-alerts</a>\n  </p>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:8px 28px 18px;background:#F1F5F9;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:10px;color:#64748B;line-height:1.4;\">\n    This is a transactional public-health alert generated by the national surveillance pipeline. Do not reply; coordinate through the escalation ladder.<br>\n    Generated 2026-04-21 18:30 UTC · template DEMO_183022 · recipient action expected within 4h.\n  </p>\n</td></tr></table></td></tr></table></body></html>', 'ALERT', 21, 'UG', 'KYOTERA', 'MUTUKULA', 'SENT', NULL, 0, '2026-04-21 18:30:36', NULL, NULL, 'CMD:demo-all', '2026-04-21 18:30:36', '2026-04-21 18:30:36'),
(231, 118, 'vexa256@gmail.com', NULL, 'EMAIL', 'TIER1_ADVISORY', '⚕ IHR Tier 1 · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) suspected · Uganda POE MUTUKULA · 24h WHO window', '\n  IHR 2005 · TIER 1 · ALWAYS NOTIFIABLE\n  A single suspected case triggers WHO notification within 24 hours.\n  ⚕ Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) — suspected case\n  Suspected VHF — returned traveller from DRC North Kivu\n  \n    Uganda · POE MUTUKULA · KYOTERA · alert DEMO_183022\n    Status OPEN · raised 2026-04-21 18:00\n  \n\n\n\n  Regulatory context. Under the International Health Regulations (2005), Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) is in the WHO Tier 1 always-notifiable list. A single laboratory-confirmed OR cl', '<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><meta charset=\"utf-8\"><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\"></head><body style=\"margin:0;padding:0;background:#EEF2F7;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;color:#0F172A;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#EEF2F7;padding:24px 12px;\"><tr><td align=\"center\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"640\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"max-width:640px;background:#FFFFFF;border-radius:10px;overflow:hidden;box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><tr><td style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,#0C1B3A 0%,#1E293B 55%,#0F172A 100%);padding:26px 28px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#FCD34D;font-weight:700;\">IHR 2005 · TIER 1 · ALWAYS NOTIFIABLE</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#E2E8F0;font-weight:600;\">A single suspected case triggers WHO notification within 24 hours.</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:12px;font-size:22px;font-weight:800;color:#FFFFFF;line-height:1.15;\">⚕ Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) — suspected case</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;font-size:14px;color:#E2E8F0;\">Suspected VHF — returned traveller from DRC North Kivu</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:14px;padding:10px 14px;background:rgba(252,211,77,0.12);border:1px solid rgba(252,211,77,0.3);border-radius:6px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#FDE68A;\"><strong>Uganda</strong> · POE MUTUKULA · KYOTERA · alert DEMO_183022</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#FCD34D;margin-top:4px;\">Status OPEN · raised 2026-04-21 18:00</div>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:22px 28px 0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Regulatory context.</strong> Under the International Health Regulations (2005), <em>Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</em> is in the WHO <strong>Tier 1 always-notifiable</strong> list. A single laboratory-confirmed OR clinically-suspected case constitutes a potential Public Health Emergency of International Concern and must be notified to WHO through the National IHR Focal Point within <strong>24 hours of detection</strong>.</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Disease profile — Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F1F5F9;border-left:4px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:6px;\">\n    <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"font-size:12px;\">\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#475569;\">WHO category</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#475569;\">Case fatality rate</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">50.0%</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#475569;\">Incubation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">2–21 days (typically 4–10)</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#475569;vertical-align:top;\">Transmission</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Direct contact with body fluids of symptomatic case or contaminated fomites; sexual transmission from survivors; bat reservoir</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#475569;vertical-align:top;\">PPE required</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">VHF full PPE: fluid-resistant coverall, double gloves, PAPR or N95+face shield, hood, boots, apron</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#475569;vertical-align:top;\">Isolation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Dedicated VHF isolation ward / treatment centre with buddy-system PPE donning/doffing</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#475569;vertical-align:top;\">IHR notification window</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;\">IMMEDIATE — any suspected VHF is a public health event of potential international concern</td></tr>\n    </table>\n    <p style=\"margin:10px 0 0;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>WHO case definition:</strong> Acute fever ≥38°C and ≥3 of: headache, vomiting, anorexia, diarrhoea, lethargy, abdominal pain, muscle/joint pain, difficulty swallowing, difficulty breathing, hiccup, OR unexplained bleeding, OR contact with suspected/confirmed case within 21 days.</p>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Tier 1 response protocol</div>\n  <ol style=\"margin:10px 0 0 20px;padding:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\"><strong>Immediate isolation</strong> of the suspected case per the disease-specific posture (Dedicated VHF isolation ward / treatment centre with buddy-system PPE donning/doffing).</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\"><strong>Full PPE</strong> for all subsequent contact (VHF full PPE: fluid-resistant coverall, double gloves, PAPR or N95+face shield, hood, boots, apron).</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\"><strong>Stop onward transport</strong> — conveyance LAND BUS-KBZ-2314, seat 14B. Quarantine contacts.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\"><strong>National IHR NFP notification</strong> within 24h. Risk assessment under Annex 2.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\"><strong>Laboratory confirmation</strong> — specimens: EDTA whole blood (5 mL), double-bagged, cold chain, dangerous-goods courier.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\"><strong>Contact tracing</strong> based on disease incubation (2–21 days (typically 4–10)).</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\"><strong>Public risk communication</strong> coordinated with national MoH / WHO country office.</li>\n  </ol>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Case dossier</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;background:#F8FAFC;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Traveller</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">A. O. · 34 y · FEMALE · Uganda</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Occupation · residence</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">Cross-border trader / market vendor · Uganda</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Travel</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">ENTRY · DR Congo → Goma</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Conveyance</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">LAND BUS-KBZ-2314 · seat 14B</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Timing</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">arrival 2026-04-21 12:30 · detected 2026-04-21 18:30</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Clinical</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">triage URGENT · emergency signs PRESENT</td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Vitals</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;background:#F8FAFC;\"><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Temperature</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;\">39.4 °C</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Pulse</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">112 bpm</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Respiratory rate</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;\">24 /min</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Blood pressure</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">98/60 mmHg</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">SpO₂</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">94 %</td></tr></table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Symptoms (8) + exposures</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;\">\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;font-size:13px;\">Symptoms PRESENT (6)</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 12px 18px;padding:0;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Bleeding gums or nose</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-21)</span> — Gums bled twice while brushing teeth</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Conjunctivitis</strong> — Bilateral scleral injection</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Continuous high-grade fever since arrival</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Retrosternal pain</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — Severe burning</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Severe fatigue</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Prostrate, unable to walk unassisted</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Very high fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — 39.4 °C at triage</li></ul><p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#047857;font-weight:600;font-size:13px;\">Explicitly ABSENT</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 4px 18px;padding:0;font-size:12px;\"><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Paralysis acute flaccid</li><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Rash vesicular pustular</li></ul><hr style=\"border:none;border-top:1px dashed #E2E8F0;margin:10px 0;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#64748B;\">[UNKNOWN]</strong> Affected healthcare facility exposure — Visited local clinic in Goma for malaria test 5d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Close contact case — Relative died of haemorrhagic illness in Butembo 12d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Consumed bushmeat</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Contact with paralysis case</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Poultry or live bird exposure</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Travel from outbreak area — Returned from DRC North Kivu via Goma</li></ul>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Red-flag findings — bedside</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Travel from EVD-affected area within 21 days</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Contact with confirmed case, body fluids, or funeral</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Haemorrhagic signs in a febrile traveller</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Conjunctival injection + retrosternal pain typical early</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Rapid progression to shock / multi-organ failure</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Differential diagnosis (4 ranked)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;\">\n    <ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#1 · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 92% · 50.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Travel from North Kivu + haemorrhagic signs + contact with deceased case in Butembo</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#2 · Marburg Virus Disease (MVD)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 48% · 50.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Cannot exclude filovirus co-differential; fruit-bat exposure not confirmed</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#3 · Severe Malaria (P. falciparum)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 30% · 20.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">Endemic — CRITICAL</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Patient from DRC with fever — rule-out required before attributing bleeding to VHF</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#4 · Lassa fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 10% · 15.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">West-Africa travel absent but pharyngitis + retrosternal pain patterns similar</div></li></ul>\n    <p style=\"margin:10px 0 0;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\"><strong>Standard differential to exclude:</strong> Marburg, Lassa, CCHF, severe malaria, typhoid, meningococcaemia, severe dengue.</p>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Immediate actions</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#0F172A;border-radius:6px;\">\n    <div style=\"color:#FCD34D;font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;font-weight:700;\">Execute now · non-negotiable</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:8px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">IMMEDIATE VHF isolation — dedicated ETU or holding isolation</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Full VHF PPE for ALL contacts (including ambulance transfer)</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">IMMEDIATE WHO IHR + AFRO notification within 24h</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Ring-vaccinate contacts with rVSV-ZEBOV if EBOV confirmed</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Line-list contacts × 21 days; safe dignified burial if deceased</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Activate national Ebola response plan</li></ul></div>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Follow-ups (14 · 1 overdue)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#0369A1;\">[IN_PROGRESS]</strong> Case investigation started <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 13:30:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Index case isolated / treatment initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 22:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Close contacts identified and listed <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Contact tracing and follow-up operational <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Coordination structure activated (EOC / PHEOC) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> WHO and partners notified per IHR Article 6 <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory specimens collected and transported <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory confirmation obtained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Epidemiological line list maintained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Risk communication to the public initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Infection prevention &amp; control (IPC) in facilities <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Vector control measures (if applicable) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Cross-border / POE surveillance strengthened <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Response resources mobilised <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:20px 28px 14px;\">\n  <div style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1E293B 0%,#0F172A 100%);border-radius:8px;padding:14px 16px;text-align:center;\">\n    <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#FCD34D;font-size:14px;font-weight:700;text-decoration:none;\">Acknowledge DEMO_183022 in POE Sentinel →</a>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:18px 28px 12px;background:#F1F5F9;border-top:1px solid #E2E8F0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:11px;color:#475569;line-height:1.5;\">\n    <strong>Uganda POE Sentinel</strong> · IHR TIER 1 ADVISORY · WHO IHR 2005 &amp; AFRO IDSR 3rd Ed. aligned.<br>\n    Alert <strong>DEMO_183022</strong> · CRITICAL — life-threatening · fired 30 minutes ago at 2026-04-21 18:00.<br>\n    Open in console → <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#1D4ED8;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;\">http://localhost/#/active-alerts</a>\n  </p>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:8px 28px 18px;background:#F1F5F9;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:10px;color:#64748B;line-height:1.4;\">\n    This is a transactional public-health alert generated by the national surveillance pipeline. Do not reply; coordinate through the escalation ladder.<br>\n    Generated 2026-04-21 18:30 UTC · template DEMO_183022 · recipient action expected within 4h.\n  </p>\n</td></tr></table></td></tr></table></body></html>', 'ALERT', 21, 'UG', 'KYOTERA', 'MUTUKULA', 'SENT', NULL, 0, '2026-04-21 18:30:38', NULL, NULL, 'CMD:demo-all', '2026-04-21 18:30:38', '2026-04-21 18:30:38');
INSERT INTO `notification_log` (`id`, `contact_id`, `to_email`, `to_phone`, `channel`, `template_code`, `subject`, `body_preview`, `body_full`, `related_entity_type`, `related_entity_id`, `country_code`, `district_code`, `poe_code`, `status`, `error_message`, `retry_count`, `sent_at`, `delivered_at`, `failed_at`, `triggered_by`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(232, 54, 'ayebare.k.timothy@gmail.com', NULL, 'EMAIL', 'TIER1_ADVISORY', '⚕ IHR Tier 1 · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) suspected · Uganda POE MUTUKULA · 24h WHO window', '\n  IHR 2005 · TIER 1 · ALWAYS NOTIFIABLE\n  A single suspected case triggers WHO notification within 24 hours.\n  ⚕ Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) — suspected case\n  Suspected VHF — returned traveller from DRC North Kivu\n  \n    Uganda · POE MUTUKULA · KYOTERA · alert DEMO_183022\n    Status OPEN · raised 2026-04-21 18:00\n  \n\n\n\n  Regulatory context. Under the International Health Regulations (2005), Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) is in the WHO Tier 1 always-notifiable list. A single laboratory-confirmed OR cl', '<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><meta charset=\"utf-8\"><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\"></head><body style=\"margin:0;padding:0;background:#EEF2F7;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;color:#0F172A;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#EEF2F7;padding:24px 12px;\"><tr><td align=\"center\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"640\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"max-width:640px;background:#FFFFFF;border-radius:10px;overflow:hidden;box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><tr><td style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,#0C1B3A 0%,#1E293B 55%,#0F172A 100%);padding:26px 28px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#FCD34D;font-weight:700;\">IHR 2005 · TIER 1 · ALWAYS NOTIFIABLE</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#E2E8F0;font-weight:600;\">A single suspected case triggers WHO notification within 24 hours.</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:12px;font-size:22px;font-weight:800;color:#FFFFFF;line-height:1.15;\">⚕ Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) — suspected case</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;font-size:14px;color:#E2E8F0;\">Suspected VHF — returned traveller from DRC North Kivu</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:14px;padding:10px 14px;background:rgba(252,211,77,0.12);border:1px solid rgba(252,211,77,0.3);border-radius:6px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#FDE68A;\"><strong>Uganda</strong> · POE MUTUKULA · KYOTERA · alert DEMO_183022</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#FCD34D;margin-top:4px;\">Status OPEN · raised 2026-04-21 18:00</div>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:22px 28px 0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Regulatory context.</strong> Under the International Health Regulations (2005), <em>Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</em> is in the WHO <strong>Tier 1 always-notifiable</strong> list. A single laboratory-confirmed OR clinically-suspected case constitutes a potential Public Health Emergency of International Concern and must be notified to WHO through the National IHR Focal Point within <strong>24 hours of detection</strong>.</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Disease profile — Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F1F5F9;border-left:4px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:6px;\">\n    <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"font-size:12px;\">\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#475569;\">WHO category</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#475569;\">Case fatality rate</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">50.0%</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#475569;\">Incubation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">2–21 days (typically 4–10)</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#475569;vertical-align:top;\">Transmission</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Direct contact with body fluids of symptomatic case or contaminated fomites; sexual transmission from survivors; bat reservoir</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#475569;vertical-align:top;\">PPE required</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">VHF full PPE: fluid-resistant coverall, double gloves, PAPR or N95+face shield, hood, boots, apron</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#475569;vertical-align:top;\">Isolation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Dedicated VHF isolation ward / treatment centre with buddy-system PPE donning/doffing</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#475569;vertical-align:top;\">IHR notification window</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;\">IMMEDIATE — any suspected VHF is a public health event of potential international concern</td></tr>\n    </table>\n    <p style=\"margin:10px 0 0;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>WHO case definition:</strong> Acute fever ≥38°C and ≥3 of: headache, vomiting, anorexia, diarrhoea, lethargy, abdominal pain, muscle/joint pain, difficulty swallowing, difficulty breathing, hiccup, OR unexplained bleeding, OR contact with suspected/confirmed case within 21 days.</p>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Tier 1 response protocol</div>\n  <ol style=\"margin:10px 0 0 20px;padding:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\"><strong>Immediate isolation</strong> of the suspected case per the disease-specific posture (Dedicated VHF isolation ward / treatment centre with buddy-system PPE donning/doffing).</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\"><strong>Full PPE</strong> for all subsequent contact (VHF full PPE: fluid-resistant coverall, double gloves, PAPR or N95+face shield, hood, boots, apron).</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\"><strong>Stop onward transport</strong> — conveyance LAND BUS-KBZ-2314, seat 14B. Quarantine contacts.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\"><strong>National IHR NFP notification</strong> within 24h. Risk assessment under Annex 2.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\"><strong>Laboratory confirmation</strong> — specimens: EDTA whole blood (5 mL), double-bagged, cold chain, dangerous-goods courier.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\"><strong>Contact tracing</strong> based on disease incubation (2–21 days (typically 4–10)).</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\"><strong>Public risk communication</strong> coordinated with national MoH / WHO country office.</li>\n  </ol>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Case dossier</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;background:#F8FAFC;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Traveller</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">A. O. · 34 y · FEMALE · Uganda</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Occupation · residence</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">Cross-border trader / market vendor · Uganda</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Travel</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">ENTRY · DR Congo → Goma</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Conveyance</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">LAND BUS-KBZ-2314 · seat 14B</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Timing</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">arrival 2026-04-21 12:30 · detected 2026-04-21 18:30</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Clinical</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">triage URGENT · emergency signs PRESENT</td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Vitals</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;background:#F8FAFC;\"><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Temperature</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;\">39.4 °C</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Pulse</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">112 bpm</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Respiratory rate</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;\">24 /min</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Blood pressure</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">98/60 mmHg</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">SpO₂</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">94 %</td></tr></table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Symptoms (8) + exposures</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;\">\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;font-size:13px;\">Symptoms PRESENT (6)</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 12px 18px;padding:0;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Bleeding gums or nose</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-21)</span> — Gums bled twice while brushing teeth</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Conjunctivitis</strong> — Bilateral scleral injection</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Continuous high-grade fever since arrival</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Retrosternal pain</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — Severe burning</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Severe fatigue</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Prostrate, unable to walk unassisted</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Very high fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — 39.4 °C at triage</li></ul><p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#047857;font-weight:600;font-size:13px;\">Explicitly ABSENT</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 4px 18px;padding:0;font-size:12px;\"><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Paralysis acute flaccid</li><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Rash vesicular pustular</li></ul><hr style=\"border:none;border-top:1px dashed #E2E8F0;margin:10px 0;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#64748B;\">[UNKNOWN]</strong> Affected healthcare facility exposure — Visited local clinic in Goma for malaria test 5d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Close contact case — Relative died of haemorrhagic illness in Butembo 12d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Consumed bushmeat</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Contact with paralysis case</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Poultry or live bird exposure</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Travel from outbreak area — Returned from DRC North Kivu via Goma</li></ul>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Red-flag findings — bedside</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Travel from EVD-affected area within 21 days</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Contact with confirmed case, body fluids, or funeral</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Haemorrhagic signs in a febrile traveller</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Conjunctival injection + retrosternal pain typical early</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Rapid progression to shock / multi-organ failure</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Differential diagnosis (4 ranked)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;\">\n    <ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#1 · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 92% · 50.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Travel from North Kivu + haemorrhagic signs + contact with deceased case in Butembo</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#2 · Marburg Virus Disease (MVD)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 48% · 50.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Cannot exclude filovirus co-differential; fruit-bat exposure not confirmed</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#3 · Severe Malaria (P. falciparum)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 30% · 20.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">Endemic — CRITICAL</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Patient from DRC with fever — rule-out required before attributing bleeding to VHF</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#4 · Lassa fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 10% · 15.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">West-Africa travel absent but pharyngitis + retrosternal pain patterns similar</div></li></ul>\n    <p style=\"margin:10px 0 0;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\"><strong>Standard differential to exclude:</strong> Marburg, Lassa, CCHF, severe malaria, typhoid, meningococcaemia, severe dengue.</p>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Immediate actions</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#0F172A;border-radius:6px;\">\n    <div style=\"color:#FCD34D;font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;font-weight:700;\">Execute now · non-negotiable</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:8px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">IMMEDIATE VHF isolation — dedicated ETU or holding isolation</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Full VHF PPE for ALL contacts (including ambulance transfer)</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">IMMEDIATE WHO IHR + AFRO notification within 24h</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Ring-vaccinate contacts with rVSV-ZEBOV if EBOV confirmed</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Line-list contacts × 21 days; safe dignified burial if deceased</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Activate national Ebola response plan</li></ul></div>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Follow-ups (14 · 1 overdue)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#0369A1;\">[IN_PROGRESS]</strong> Case investigation started <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 13:30:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Index case isolated / treatment initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 22:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Close contacts identified and listed <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Contact tracing and follow-up operational <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Coordination structure activated (EOC / PHEOC) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> WHO and partners notified per IHR Article 6 <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory specimens collected and transported <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory confirmation obtained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Epidemiological line list maintained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Risk communication to the public initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Infection prevention &amp; control (IPC) in facilities <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Vector control measures (if applicable) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Cross-border / POE surveillance strengthened <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Response resources mobilised <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:20px 28px 14px;\">\n  <div style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1E293B 0%,#0F172A 100%);border-radius:8px;padding:14px 16px;text-align:center;\">\n    <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#FCD34D;font-size:14px;font-weight:700;text-decoration:none;\">Acknowledge DEMO_183022 in POE Sentinel →</a>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:18px 28px 12px;background:#F1F5F9;border-top:1px solid #E2E8F0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:11px;color:#475569;line-height:1.5;\">\n    <strong>Uganda POE Sentinel</strong> · IHR TIER 1 ADVISORY · WHO IHR 2005 &amp; AFRO IDSR 3rd Ed. aligned.<br>\n    Alert <strong>DEMO_183022</strong> · CRITICAL — life-threatening · fired 30 minutes ago at 2026-04-21 18:00.<br>\n    Open in console → <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#1D4ED8;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;\">http://localhost/#/active-alerts</a>\n  </p>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:8px 28px 18px;background:#F1F5F9;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:10px;color:#64748B;line-height:1.4;\">\n    This is a transactional public-health alert generated by the national surveillance pipeline. Do not reply; coordinate through the escalation ladder.<br>\n    Generated 2026-04-21 18:30 UTC · template DEMO_183022 · recipient action expected within 4h.\n  </p>\n</td></tr></table></td></tr></table></body></html>', 'ALERT', 21, 'UG', 'KYOTERA', 'MUTUKULA', 'SENT', NULL, 0, '2026-04-21 18:30:40', NULL, NULL, 'CMD:demo-all', '2026-04-21 18:30:40', '2026-04-21 18:30:40'),
(233, 119, 'ecsahccloudsurveillancealerts@gmail.com', NULL, 'EMAIL', 'TIER1_ADVISORY', '⚕ IHR Tier 1 · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) suspected · Uganda POE MUTUKULA · 24h WHO window', '\n  IHR 2005 · TIER 1 · ALWAYS NOTIFIABLE\n  A single suspected case triggers WHO notification within 24 hours.\n  ⚕ Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) — suspected case\n  Suspected VHF — returned traveller from DRC North Kivu\n  \n    Uganda · POE MUTUKULA · KYOTERA · alert DEMO_183022\n    Status OPEN · raised 2026-04-21 18:00\n  \n\n\n\n  Regulatory context. Under the International Health Regulations (2005), Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) is in the WHO Tier 1 always-notifiable list. A single laboratory-confirmed OR cl', '<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><meta charset=\"utf-8\"><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\"></head><body style=\"margin:0;padding:0;background:#EEF2F7;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;color:#0F172A;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#EEF2F7;padding:24px 12px;\"><tr><td align=\"center\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"640\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"max-width:640px;background:#FFFFFF;border-radius:10px;overflow:hidden;box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><tr><td style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,#0C1B3A 0%,#1E293B 55%,#0F172A 100%);padding:26px 28px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#FCD34D;font-weight:700;\">IHR 2005 · TIER 1 · ALWAYS NOTIFIABLE</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#E2E8F0;font-weight:600;\">A single suspected case triggers WHO notification within 24 hours.</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:12px;font-size:22px;font-weight:800;color:#FFFFFF;line-height:1.15;\">⚕ Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) — suspected case</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;font-size:14px;color:#E2E8F0;\">Suspected VHF — returned traveller from DRC North Kivu</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:14px;padding:10px 14px;background:rgba(252,211,77,0.12);border:1px solid rgba(252,211,77,0.3);border-radius:6px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#FDE68A;\"><strong>Uganda</strong> · POE MUTUKULA · KYOTERA · alert DEMO_183022</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#FCD34D;margin-top:4px;\">Status OPEN · raised 2026-04-21 18:00</div>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:22px 28px 0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Regulatory context.</strong> Under the International Health Regulations (2005), <em>Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</em> is in the WHO <strong>Tier 1 always-notifiable</strong> list. A single laboratory-confirmed OR clinically-suspected case constitutes a potential Public Health Emergency of International Concern and must be notified to WHO through the National IHR Focal Point within <strong>24 hours of detection</strong>.</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Disease profile — Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F1F5F9;border-left:4px solid #FCD34D;border-radius:6px;\">\n    <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"font-size:12px;\">\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#475569;\">WHO category</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#475569;\">Case fatality rate</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">50.0%</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#475569;\">Incubation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">2–21 days (typically 4–10)</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#475569;vertical-align:top;\">Transmission</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Direct contact with body fluids of symptomatic case or contaminated fomites; sexual transmission from survivors; bat reservoir</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#475569;vertical-align:top;\">PPE required</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">VHF full PPE: fluid-resistant coverall, double gloves, PAPR or N95+face shield, hood, boots, apron</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#475569;vertical-align:top;\">Isolation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Dedicated VHF isolation ward / treatment centre with buddy-system PPE donning/doffing</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#475569;vertical-align:top;\">IHR notification window</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;\">IMMEDIATE — any suspected VHF is a public health event of potential international concern</td></tr>\n    </table>\n    <p style=\"margin:10px 0 0;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>WHO case definition:</strong> Acute fever ≥38°C and ≥3 of: headache, vomiting, anorexia, diarrhoea, lethargy, abdominal pain, muscle/joint pain, difficulty swallowing, difficulty breathing, hiccup, OR unexplained bleeding, OR contact with suspected/confirmed case within 21 days.</p>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Tier 1 response protocol</div>\n  <ol style=\"margin:10px 0 0 20px;padding:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\"><strong>Immediate isolation</strong> of the suspected case per the disease-specific posture (Dedicated VHF isolation ward / treatment centre with buddy-system PPE donning/doffing).</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\"><strong>Full PPE</strong> for all subsequent contact (VHF full PPE: fluid-resistant coverall, double gloves, PAPR or N95+face shield, hood, boots, apron).</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\"><strong>Stop onward transport</strong> — conveyance LAND BUS-KBZ-2314, seat 14B. Quarantine contacts.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\"><strong>National IHR NFP notification</strong> within 24h. Risk assessment under Annex 2.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\"><strong>Laboratory confirmation</strong> — specimens: EDTA whole blood (5 mL), double-bagged, cold chain, dangerous-goods courier.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\"><strong>Contact tracing</strong> based on disease incubation (2–21 days (typically 4–10)).</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\"><strong>Public risk communication</strong> coordinated with national MoH / WHO country office.</li>\n  </ol>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Case dossier</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;background:#F8FAFC;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Traveller</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">A. O. · 34 y · FEMALE · Uganda</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Occupation · residence</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">Cross-border trader / market vendor · Uganda</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Travel</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">ENTRY · DR Congo → Goma</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Conveyance</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">LAND BUS-KBZ-2314 · seat 14B</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Timing</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">arrival 2026-04-21 12:30 · detected 2026-04-21 18:30</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Clinical</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">triage URGENT · emergency signs PRESENT</td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Vitals</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;background:#F8FAFC;\"><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Temperature</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;\">39.4 °C</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Pulse</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">112 bpm</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Respiratory rate</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;\">24 /min</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Blood pressure</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">98/60 mmHg</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">SpO₂</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">94 %</td></tr></table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Symptoms (8) + exposures</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;\">\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;font-size:13px;\">Symptoms PRESENT (6)</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 12px 18px;padding:0;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Bleeding gums or nose</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-21)</span> — Gums bled twice while brushing teeth</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Conjunctivitis</strong> — Bilateral scleral injection</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Continuous high-grade fever since arrival</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Retrosternal pain</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — Severe burning</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Severe fatigue</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Prostrate, unable to walk unassisted</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Very high fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — 39.4 °C at triage</li></ul><p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#047857;font-weight:600;font-size:13px;\">Explicitly ABSENT</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 4px 18px;padding:0;font-size:12px;\"><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Paralysis acute flaccid</li><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Rash vesicular pustular</li></ul><hr style=\"border:none;border-top:1px dashed #E2E8F0;margin:10px 0;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#64748B;\">[UNKNOWN]</strong> Affected healthcare facility exposure — Visited local clinic in Goma for malaria test 5d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Close contact case — Relative died of haemorrhagic illness in Butembo 12d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Consumed bushmeat</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Contact with paralysis case</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Poultry or live bird exposure</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Travel from outbreak area — Returned from DRC North Kivu via Goma</li></ul>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Red-flag findings — bedside</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Travel from EVD-affected area within 21 days</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Contact with confirmed case, body fluids, or funeral</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Haemorrhagic signs in a febrile traveller</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Conjunctival injection + retrosternal pain typical early</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Rapid progression to shock / multi-organ failure</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Differential diagnosis (4 ranked)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;\">\n    <ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#1 · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 92% · 50.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Travel from North Kivu + haemorrhagic signs + contact with deceased case in Butembo</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#2 · Marburg Virus Disease (MVD)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 48% · 50.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Cannot exclude filovirus co-differential; fruit-bat exposure not confirmed</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#3 · Severe Malaria (P. falciparum)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 30% · 20.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">Endemic — CRITICAL</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Patient from DRC with fever — rule-out required before attributing bleeding to VHF</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#4 · Lassa fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 10% · 15.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">West-Africa travel absent but pharyngitis + retrosternal pain patterns similar</div></li></ul>\n    <p style=\"margin:10px 0 0;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\"><strong>Standard differential to exclude:</strong> Marburg, Lassa, CCHF, severe malaria, typhoid, meningococcaemia, severe dengue.</p>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Immediate actions</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#0F172A;border-radius:6px;\">\n    <div style=\"color:#FCD34D;font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;font-weight:700;\">Execute now · non-negotiable</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:8px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">IMMEDIATE VHF isolation — dedicated ETU or holding isolation</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Full VHF PPE for ALL contacts (including ambulance transfer)</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">IMMEDIATE WHO IHR + AFRO notification within 24h</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Ring-vaccinate contacts with rVSV-ZEBOV if EBOV confirmed</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Line-list contacts × 21 days; safe dignified burial if deceased</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\">Activate national Ebola response plan</li></ul></div>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C1B3A;font-weight:800;\">Follow-ups (14 · 1 overdue)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#0369A1;\">[IN_PROGRESS]</strong> Case investigation started <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 13:30:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Index case isolated / treatment initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 22:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Close contacts identified and listed <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Contact tracing and follow-up operational <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Coordination structure activated (EOC / PHEOC) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> WHO and partners notified per IHR Article 6 <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory specimens collected and transported <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory confirmation obtained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Epidemiological line list maintained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Risk communication to the public initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Infection prevention &amp; control (IPC) in facilities <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Vector control measures (if applicable) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Cross-border / POE surveillance strengthened <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Response resources mobilised <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:20px 28px 14px;\">\n  <div style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1E293B 0%,#0F172A 100%);border-radius:8px;padding:14px 16px;text-align:center;\">\n    <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#FCD34D;font-size:14px;font-weight:700;text-decoration:none;\">Acknowledge DEMO_183022 in POE Sentinel →</a>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:18px 28px 12px;background:#F1F5F9;border-top:1px solid #E2E8F0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:11px;color:#475569;line-height:1.5;\">\n    <strong>Uganda POE Sentinel</strong> · IHR TIER 1 ADVISORY · WHO IHR 2005 &amp; AFRO IDSR 3rd Ed. aligned.<br>\n    Alert <strong>DEMO_183022</strong> · CRITICAL — life-threatening · fired 30 minutes ago at 2026-04-21 18:00.<br>\n    Open in console → <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#1D4ED8;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;\">http://localhost/#/active-alerts</a>\n  </p>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:8px 28px 18px;background:#F1F5F9;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:10px;color:#64748B;line-height:1.4;\">\n    This is a transactional public-health alert generated by the national surveillance pipeline. Do not reply; coordinate through the escalation ladder.<br>\n    Generated 2026-04-21 18:30 UTC · template DEMO_183022 · recipient action expected within 4h.\n  </p>\n</td></tr></table></td></tr></table></body></html>', 'ALERT', 21, 'UG', 'KYOTERA', 'MUTUKULA', 'SENT', NULL, 0, '2026-04-21 18:30:42', NULL, NULL, 'CMD:demo-all', '2026-04-21 18:30:42', '2026-04-21 18:30:42');
INSERT INTO `notification_log` (`id`, `contact_id`, `to_email`, `to_phone`, `channel`, `template_code`, `subject`, `body_preview`, `body_full`, `related_entity_type`, `related_entity_id`, `country_code`, `district_code`, `poe_code`, `status`, `error_message`, `retry_count`, `sent_at`, `delivered_at`, `failed_at`, `triggered_by`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(234, 118, 'vexa256@gmail.com', NULL, 'EMAIL', 'ANNEX2_HIT', '◆ IHR Annex 2 criteria met · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · Uganda POE MUTUKULA', '\n  IHR 2005 · ANNEX 2 DECISION INSTRUMENT\n  Event may constitute a public-health emergency of international concern.\n  ◆ Annex 2 criteria met — assess &amp; notify\n  Suspected VHF — returned traveller from DRC North Kivu\n\n\n\n  This event was flagged against the WHO IHR Annex 2 Decision Instrument. At least one Annex 2 pillar has fired and a national risk assessment is required. If 2 or more criteria are confirmed, the event must be notified to WHO through the National IHR Focal Point.\n\n\n\n  The fo', '<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><meta charset=\"utf-8\"><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\"></head><body style=\"margin:0;padding:0;background:#EEF2F7;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;color:#0F172A;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#EEF2F7;padding:24px 12px;\"><tr><td align=\"center\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"640\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"max-width:640px;background:#FFFFFF;border-radius:10px;overflow:hidden;box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><tr><td style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,#4C1D95 0%,#5B21B6 55%,#7C3AED 100%);padding:26px 28px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#E9D5FF;font-weight:700;\">IHR 2005 · ANNEX 2 DECISION INSTRUMENT</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#EDE9FE;font-weight:600;\">Event may constitute a public-health emergency of international concern.</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:12px;font-size:22px;font-weight:800;color:#FFFFFF;line-height:1.15;\">◆ Annex 2 criteria met — assess &amp; notify</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;font-size:14px;color:#EDE9FE;\">Suspected VHF — returned traveller from DRC North Kivu</div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:22px 28px 0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">This event was flagged against the WHO IHR Annex 2 Decision Instrument. At least one Annex 2 pillar has fired and a national risk assessment is required. If 2 or more criteria are confirmed, the event must be notified to WHO through the National IHR Focal Point.</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#5B21B6;font-weight:800;\">The four Annex 2 criteria</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;background:#F5F3FF;border:1px solid #DDD6FE;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <tr>\n      <td style=\"padding:10px 14px;border-bottom:1px solid #DDD6FE;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.06em;color:#6D28D9;font-weight:700;\">1 · Serious public-health impact</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;margin-top:2px;\">High case-fatality, rapid progression, vulnerable populations, healthcare system strain.</div>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td style=\"padding:10px 14px;border-bottom:1px solid #DDD6FE;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.06em;color:#6D28D9;font-weight:700;\">2 · Unusual / unexpected</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;margin-top:2px;\">Unknown aetiology, unusual clinical course, unexpected geographical spread, emergence of resistance.</div>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td style=\"padding:10px 14px;border-bottom:1px solid #DDD6FE;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.06em;color:#6D28D9;font-weight:700;\">3 · Significant risk of international spread</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;margin-top:2px;\">Evidence of cross-border transmission, infected travellers, contaminated conveyances, contacts crossing borders.</div>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td style=\"padding:10px 14px;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.06em;color:#6D28D9;font-weight:700;\">4 · Significant risk of international travel / trade restrictions</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;margin-top:2px;\">Event likely to prompt other states to restrict movement / trade / conveyances.</div>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n  </table>\n  <p style=\"margin:8px 0 0;font-size:11px;color:#5B21B6;\"><strong>Rule of thumb:</strong> if any 2 of the 4 criteria apply → WHO notification is mandatory within 24 hours.</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#5B21B6;font-weight:800;\">Event context</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;background:#F8FAFC;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Alert · country · POE</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">DEMO_183022 · Uganda · MUTUKULA</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Suspected disease</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">CFR</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">50.0%</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Traveller</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">A. O. · 34 y · Uganda → Uganda</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Travel path</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">DR Congo → Goma → MUTUKULA</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Conveyance · seat</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">LAND BUS-KBZ-2314 · seat 14B</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Detected</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">2026-04-21 18:30 · Ayebare Timothy</td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#5B21B6;font-weight:800;\">Cross-border spread signal</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F5F3FF;border:1px solid #DDD6FE;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\">Travel history on file:</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>VISITED</strong> · DR Congo <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(2026-04-03 → 2026-04-19)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>TRANSIT</strong> · Rwanda <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(2026-04-19 → 2026-04-20)</span></li></ul></div>\n    <p style=\"margin:10px 0 0;font-size:12px;color:#5B21B6;\"><em>Every country listed must be considered for cross-border notification to their IHR NFP if the case is confirmed.</em></p>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#5B21B6;font-weight:800;\">Clinical evidence</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;font-size:12px;\"><strong>Syndrome:</strong> VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER · <strong>triage:</strong> URGENT · <strong>ER signs:</strong> PRESENT</p>\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;font-size:13px;\">Symptoms PRESENT (6)</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 12px 18px;padding:0;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Bleeding gums or nose</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-21)</span> — Gums bled twice while brushing teeth</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Conjunctivitis</strong> — Bilateral scleral injection</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Continuous high-grade fever since arrival</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Retrosternal pain</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — Severe burning</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Severe fatigue</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Prostrate, unable to walk unassisted</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Very high fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — 39.4 °C at triage</li></ul><p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#047857;font-weight:600;font-size:13px;\">Explicitly ABSENT</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 4px 18px;padding:0;font-size:12px;\"><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Paralysis acute flaccid</li><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Rash vesicular pustular</li></ul>\n    <hr style=\"border:none;border-top:1px dashed #E2E8F0;margin:10px 0;\">\n    <ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#64748B;\">[UNKNOWN]</strong> Affected healthcare facility exposure — Visited local clinic in Goma for malaria test 5d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Close contact case — Relative died of haemorrhagic illness in Butembo 12d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Consumed bushmeat</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Contact with paralysis case</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Poultry or live bird exposure</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Travel from outbreak area — Returned from DRC North Kivu via Goma</li></ul>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#FEF3C7;border-left:4px solid #B45309;border-radius:6px;margin:12px 0;\">\n  <tr><td style=\"padding:14px 16px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;color:#92400E;font-weight:700;\">Disease intelligence</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:17px;font-weight:700;color:#0F172A;margin:4px 0 2px;\">Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#475569;margin-bottom:10px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div>\n    <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\">\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;\">Case fatality rate</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">50.0%</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;\">Incubation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">2–21 days (typically 4–10)</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">Transmission</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Direct contact with body fluids of symptomatic case or contaminated fomites; sexual transmission from survivors; bat reservoir</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">PPE</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">VHF full PPE: fluid-resistant coverall, double gloves, PAPR or N95+face shield, hood, boots, apron</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">Isolation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Dedicated VHF isolation ward / treatment centre with buddy-system PPE donning/doffing</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">IHR notification</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">IMMEDIATE — any suspected VHF is a public health event of potential international concern</td></tr>\n    </table>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:10px;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>WHO case definition:</strong> Acute fever ≥38°C and ≥3 of: headache, vomiting, anorexia, diarrhoea, lethargy, abdominal pain, muscle/joint pain, difficulty swallowing, difficulty breathing, hiccup, OR unexplained bleeding, OR contact with suspected/confirmed case within 21 days.</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Differential:</strong> Marburg, Lassa, CCHF, severe malaria, typhoid, meningococcaemia, severe dengue</div>\n  </td></tr>\n</table></td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:0 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#5B21B6;font-weight:800;\">Expected actions — NATIONAL IHR NFP</div>\n  <ol style=\"margin:10px 0 0 20px;padding:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\">Complete Annex 2 decision instrument within <strong>48 hours</strong>.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\">Coordinate multi-sectoral risk assessment (MoH + IHR NFP + PHEOC).</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\">If 2+ criteria confirmed → submit IHR notification to WHO within <strong>24 hours</strong>.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\">Pre-warn neighbouring country IHR NFPs if cross-border spread plausible.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\">Initiate appropriate border-health measures (screening, tracing, quarantine).</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\">Prepare public risk communication with WHO country office.</li>\n  </ol>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#5B21B6;font-weight:800;\">Current follow-up obligations (14)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#0369A1;\">[IN_PROGRESS]</strong> Case investigation started <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 13:30:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Index case isolated / treatment initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 22:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Close contacts identified and listed <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Contact tracing and follow-up operational <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Coordination structure activated (EOC / PHEOC) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> WHO and partners notified per IHR Article 6 <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory specimens collected and transported <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory confirmation obtained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Epidemiological line list maintained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Risk communication to the public initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Infection prevention &amp; control (IPC) in facilities <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Vector control measures (if applicable) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Cross-border / POE surveillance strengthened <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Response resources mobilised <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:20px 28px 14px;\">\n  <div style=\"background:#5B21B6;border-radius:8px;padding:14px 16px;text-align:center;\">\n    <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#FFFFFF;font-size:14px;font-weight:700;text-decoration:none;\">Complete Annex 2 assessment →</a>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:18px 28px 12px;background:#F1F5F9;border-top:1px solid #E2E8F0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:11px;color:#475569;line-height:1.5;\">\n    <strong>Uganda POE Sentinel</strong> · IHR ANNEX 2 ASSESSMENT · WHO IHR 2005 &amp; AFRO IDSR 3rd Ed. aligned.<br>\n    Alert <strong>DEMO_183022</strong> · CRITICAL — life-threatening · fired 30 minutes ago at 2026-04-21 18:00.<br>\n    Open in console → <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#1D4ED8;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;\">http://localhost/#/active-alerts</a>\n  </p>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:8px 28px 18px;background:#F1F5F9;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:10px;color:#64748B;line-height:1.4;\">\n    This is a transactional public-health alert generated by the national surveillance pipeline. Do not reply; coordinate through the escalation ladder.<br>\n    Generated 2026-04-21 18:30 UTC · template DEMO_183022 · recipient action expected within 4h.\n  </p>\n</td></tr></table></td></tr></table></body></html>', 'ALERT', 21, 'UG', 'KYOTERA', 'MUTUKULA', 'SENT', NULL, 0, '2026-04-21 18:30:44', NULL, NULL, 'CMD:demo-all', '2026-04-21 18:30:44', '2026-04-21 18:30:44'),
(235, 54, 'ayebare.k.timothy@gmail.com', NULL, 'EMAIL', 'ANNEX2_HIT', '◆ IHR Annex 2 criteria met · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · Uganda POE MUTUKULA', '\n  IHR 2005 · ANNEX 2 DECISION INSTRUMENT\n  Event may constitute a public-health emergency of international concern.\n  ◆ Annex 2 criteria met — assess &amp; notify\n  Suspected VHF — returned traveller from DRC North Kivu\n\n\n\n  This event was flagged against the WHO IHR Annex 2 Decision Instrument. At least one Annex 2 pillar has fired and a national risk assessment is required. If 2 or more criteria are confirmed, the event must be notified to WHO through the National IHR Focal Point.\n\n\n\n  The fo', '<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><meta charset=\"utf-8\"><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\"></head><body style=\"margin:0;padding:0;background:#EEF2F7;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;color:#0F172A;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#EEF2F7;padding:24px 12px;\"><tr><td align=\"center\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"640\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"max-width:640px;background:#FFFFFF;border-radius:10px;overflow:hidden;box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><tr><td style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,#4C1D95 0%,#5B21B6 55%,#7C3AED 100%);padding:26px 28px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#E9D5FF;font-weight:700;\">IHR 2005 · ANNEX 2 DECISION INSTRUMENT</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#EDE9FE;font-weight:600;\">Event may constitute a public-health emergency of international concern.</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:12px;font-size:22px;font-weight:800;color:#FFFFFF;line-height:1.15;\">◆ Annex 2 criteria met — assess &amp; notify</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;font-size:14px;color:#EDE9FE;\">Suspected VHF — returned traveller from DRC North Kivu</div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:22px 28px 0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">This event was flagged against the WHO IHR Annex 2 Decision Instrument. At least one Annex 2 pillar has fired and a national risk assessment is required. If 2 or more criteria are confirmed, the event must be notified to WHO through the National IHR Focal Point.</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#5B21B6;font-weight:800;\">The four Annex 2 criteria</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;background:#F5F3FF;border:1px solid #DDD6FE;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <tr>\n      <td style=\"padding:10px 14px;border-bottom:1px solid #DDD6FE;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.06em;color:#6D28D9;font-weight:700;\">1 · Serious public-health impact</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;margin-top:2px;\">High case-fatality, rapid progression, vulnerable populations, healthcare system strain.</div>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td style=\"padding:10px 14px;border-bottom:1px solid #DDD6FE;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.06em;color:#6D28D9;font-weight:700;\">2 · Unusual / unexpected</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;margin-top:2px;\">Unknown aetiology, unusual clinical course, unexpected geographical spread, emergence of resistance.</div>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td style=\"padding:10px 14px;border-bottom:1px solid #DDD6FE;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.06em;color:#6D28D9;font-weight:700;\">3 · Significant risk of international spread</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;margin-top:2px;\">Evidence of cross-border transmission, infected travellers, contaminated conveyances, contacts crossing borders.</div>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td style=\"padding:10px 14px;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.06em;color:#6D28D9;font-weight:700;\">4 · Significant risk of international travel / trade restrictions</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;margin-top:2px;\">Event likely to prompt other states to restrict movement / trade / conveyances.</div>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n  </table>\n  <p style=\"margin:8px 0 0;font-size:11px;color:#5B21B6;\"><strong>Rule of thumb:</strong> if any 2 of the 4 criteria apply → WHO notification is mandatory within 24 hours.</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#5B21B6;font-weight:800;\">Event context</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;background:#F8FAFC;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Alert · country · POE</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">DEMO_183022 · Uganda · MUTUKULA</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Suspected disease</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">CFR</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">50.0%</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Traveller</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">A. O. · 34 y · Uganda → Uganda</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Travel path</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">DR Congo → Goma → MUTUKULA</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Conveyance · seat</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">LAND BUS-KBZ-2314 · seat 14B</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Detected</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">2026-04-21 18:30 · Ayebare Timothy</td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#5B21B6;font-weight:800;\">Cross-border spread signal</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F5F3FF;border:1px solid #DDD6FE;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\">Travel history on file:</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>VISITED</strong> · DR Congo <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(2026-04-03 → 2026-04-19)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>TRANSIT</strong> · Rwanda <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(2026-04-19 → 2026-04-20)</span></li></ul></div>\n    <p style=\"margin:10px 0 0;font-size:12px;color:#5B21B6;\"><em>Every country listed must be considered for cross-border notification to their IHR NFP if the case is confirmed.</em></p>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#5B21B6;font-weight:800;\">Clinical evidence</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;font-size:12px;\"><strong>Syndrome:</strong> VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER · <strong>triage:</strong> URGENT · <strong>ER signs:</strong> PRESENT</p>\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;font-size:13px;\">Symptoms PRESENT (6)</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 12px 18px;padding:0;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Bleeding gums or nose</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-21)</span> — Gums bled twice while brushing teeth</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Conjunctivitis</strong> — Bilateral scleral injection</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Continuous high-grade fever since arrival</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Retrosternal pain</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — Severe burning</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Severe fatigue</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Prostrate, unable to walk unassisted</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Very high fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — 39.4 °C at triage</li></ul><p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#047857;font-weight:600;font-size:13px;\">Explicitly ABSENT</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 4px 18px;padding:0;font-size:12px;\"><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Paralysis acute flaccid</li><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Rash vesicular pustular</li></ul>\n    <hr style=\"border:none;border-top:1px dashed #E2E8F0;margin:10px 0;\">\n    <ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#64748B;\">[UNKNOWN]</strong> Affected healthcare facility exposure — Visited local clinic in Goma for malaria test 5d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Close contact case — Relative died of haemorrhagic illness in Butembo 12d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Consumed bushmeat</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Contact with paralysis case</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Poultry or live bird exposure</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Travel from outbreak area — Returned from DRC North Kivu via Goma</li></ul>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#FEF3C7;border-left:4px solid #B45309;border-radius:6px;margin:12px 0;\">\n  <tr><td style=\"padding:14px 16px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;color:#92400E;font-weight:700;\">Disease intelligence</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:17px;font-weight:700;color:#0F172A;margin:4px 0 2px;\">Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#475569;margin-bottom:10px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div>\n    <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\">\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;\">Case fatality rate</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">50.0%</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;\">Incubation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">2–21 days (typically 4–10)</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">Transmission</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Direct contact with body fluids of symptomatic case or contaminated fomites; sexual transmission from survivors; bat reservoir</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">PPE</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">VHF full PPE: fluid-resistant coverall, double gloves, PAPR or N95+face shield, hood, boots, apron</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">Isolation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Dedicated VHF isolation ward / treatment centre with buddy-system PPE donning/doffing</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">IHR notification</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">IMMEDIATE — any suspected VHF is a public health event of potential international concern</td></tr>\n    </table>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:10px;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>WHO case definition:</strong> Acute fever ≥38°C and ≥3 of: headache, vomiting, anorexia, diarrhoea, lethargy, abdominal pain, muscle/joint pain, difficulty swallowing, difficulty breathing, hiccup, OR unexplained bleeding, OR contact with suspected/confirmed case within 21 days.</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Differential:</strong> Marburg, Lassa, CCHF, severe malaria, typhoid, meningococcaemia, severe dengue</div>\n  </td></tr>\n</table></td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:0 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#5B21B6;font-weight:800;\">Expected actions — NATIONAL IHR NFP</div>\n  <ol style=\"margin:10px 0 0 20px;padding:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\">Complete Annex 2 decision instrument within <strong>48 hours</strong>.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\">Coordinate multi-sectoral risk assessment (MoH + IHR NFP + PHEOC).</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\">If 2+ criteria confirmed → submit IHR notification to WHO within <strong>24 hours</strong>.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\">Pre-warn neighbouring country IHR NFPs if cross-border spread plausible.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\">Initiate appropriate border-health measures (screening, tracing, quarantine).</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\">Prepare public risk communication with WHO country office.</li>\n  </ol>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#5B21B6;font-weight:800;\">Current follow-up obligations (14)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#0369A1;\">[IN_PROGRESS]</strong> Case investigation started <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 13:30:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Index case isolated / treatment initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 22:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Close contacts identified and listed <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Contact tracing and follow-up operational <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Coordination structure activated (EOC / PHEOC) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> WHO and partners notified per IHR Article 6 <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory specimens collected and transported <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory confirmation obtained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Epidemiological line list maintained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Risk communication to the public initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Infection prevention &amp; control (IPC) in facilities <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Vector control measures (if applicable) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Cross-border / POE surveillance strengthened <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Response resources mobilised <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:20px 28px 14px;\">\n  <div style=\"background:#5B21B6;border-radius:8px;padding:14px 16px;text-align:center;\">\n    <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#FFFFFF;font-size:14px;font-weight:700;text-decoration:none;\">Complete Annex 2 assessment →</a>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:18px 28px 12px;background:#F1F5F9;border-top:1px solid #E2E8F0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:11px;color:#475569;line-height:1.5;\">\n    <strong>Uganda POE Sentinel</strong> · IHR ANNEX 2 ASSESSMENT · WHO IHR 2005 &amp; AFRO IDSR 3rd Ed. aligned.<br>\n    Alert <strong>DEMO_183022</strong> · CRITICAL — life-threatening · fired 30 minutes ago at 2026-04-21 18:00.<br>\n    Open in console → <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#1D4ED8;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;\">http://localhost/#/active-alerts</a>\n  </p>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:8px 28px 18px;background:#F1F5F9;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:10px;color:#64748B;line-height:1.4;\">\n    This is a transactional public-health alert generated by the national surveillance pipeline. Do not reply; coordinate through the escalation ladder.<br>\n    Generated 2026-04-21 18:30 UTC · template DEMO_183022 · recipient action expected within 4h.\n  </p>\n</td></tr></table></td></tr></table></body></html>', 'ALERT', 21, 'UG', 'KYOTERA', 'MUTUKULA', 'SENT', NULL, 0, '2026-04-21 18:30:46', NULL, NULL, 'CMD:demo-all', '2026-04-21 18:30:46', '2026-04-21 18:30:46');
INSERT INTO `notification_log` (`id`, `contact_id`, `to_email`, `to_phone`, `channel`, `template_code`, `subject`, `body_preview`, `body_full`, `related_entity_type`, `related_entity_id`, `country_code`, `district_code`, `poe_code`, `status`, `error_message`, `retry_count`, `sent_at`, `delivered_at`, `failed_at`, `triggered_by`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(236, 119, 'ecsahccloudsurveillancealerts@gmail.com', NULL, 'EMAIL', 'ANNEX2_HIT', '◆ IHR Annex 2 criteria met · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · Uganda POE MUTUKULA', '\n  IHR 2005 · ANNEX 2 DECISION INSTRUMENT\n  Event may constitute a public-health emergency of international concern.\n  ◆ Annex 2 criteria met — assess &amp; notify\n  Suspected VHF — returned traveller from DRC North Kivu\n\n\n\n  This event was flagged against the WHO IHR Annex 2 Decision Instrument. At least one Annex 2 pillar has fired and a national risk assessment is required. If 2 or more criteria are confirmed, the event must be notified to WHO through the National IHR Focal Point.\n\n\n\n  The fo', '<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><meta charset=\"utf-8\"><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\"></head><body style=\"margin:0;padding:0;background:#EEF2F7;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;color:#0F172A;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#EEF2F7;padding:24px 12px;\"><tr><td align=\"center\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"640\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"max-width:640px;background:#FFFFFF;border-radius:10px;overflow:hidden;box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><tr><td style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,#4C1D95 0%,#5B21B6 55%,#7C3AED 100%);padding:26px 28px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#E9D5FF;font-weight:700;\">IHR 2005 · ANNEX 2 DECISION INSTRUMENT</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#EDE9FE;font-weight:600;\">Event may constitute a public-health emergency of international concern.</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:12px;font-size:22px;font-weight:800;color:#FFFFFF;line-height:1.15;\">◆ Annex 2 criteria met — assess &amp; notify</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;font-size:14px;color:#EDE9FE;\">Suspected VHF — returned traveller from DRC North Kivu</div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:22px 28px 0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">This event was flagged against the WHO IHR Annex 2 Decision Instrument. At least one Annex 2 pillar has fired and a national risk assessment is required. If 2 or more criteria are confirmed, the event must be notified to WHO through the National IHR Focal Point.</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#5B21B6;font-weight:800;\">The four Annex 2 criteria</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;background:#F5F3FF;border:1px solid #DDD6FE;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <tr>\n      <td style=\"padding:10px 14px;border-bottom:1px solid #DDD6FE;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.06em;color:#6D28D9;font-weight:700;\">1 · Serious public-health impact</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;margin-top:2px;\">High case-fatality, rapid progression, vulnerable populations, healthcare system strain.</div>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td style=\"padding:10px 14px;border-bottom:1px solid #DDD6FE;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.06em;color:#6D28D9;font-weight:700;\">2 · Unusual / unexpected</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;margin-top:2px;\">Unknown aetiology, unusual clinical course, unexpected geographical spread, emergence of resistance.</div>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td style=\"padding:10px 14px;border-bottom:1px solid #DDD6FE;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.06em;color:#6D28D9;font-weight:700;\">3 · Significant risk of international spread</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;margin-top:2px;\">Evidence of cross-border transmission, infected travellers, contaminated conveyances, contacts crossing borders.</div>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td style=\"padding:10px 14px;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.06em;color:#6D28D9;font-weight:700;\">4 · Significant risk of international travel / trade restrictions</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;margin-top:2px;\">Event likely to prompt other states to restrict movement / trade / conveyances.</div>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n  </table>\n  <p style=\"margin:8px 0 0;font-size:11px;color:#5B21B6;\"><strong>Rule of thumb:</strong> if any 2 of the 4 criteria apply → WHO notification is mandatory within 24 hours.</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#5B21B6;font-weight:800;\">Event context</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;background:#F8FAFC;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Alert · country · POE</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">DEMO_183022 · Uganda · MUTUKULA</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Suspected disease</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">CFR</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">50.0%</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Traveller</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">A. O. · 34 y · Uganda → Uganda</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Travel path</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">DR Congo → Goma → MUTUKULA</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Conveyance · seat</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">LAND BUS-KBZ-2314 · seat 14B</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Detected</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">2026-04-21 18:30 · Ayebare Timothy</td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#5B21B6;font-weight:800;\">Cross-border spread signal</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F5F3FF;border:1px solid #DDD6FE;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\">Travel history on file:</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>VISITED</strong> · DR Congo <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(2026-04-03 → 2026-04-19)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>TRANSIT</strong> · Rwanda <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(2026-04-19 → 2026-04-20)</span></li></ul></div>\n    <p style=\"margin:10px 0 0;font-size:12px;color:#5B21B6;\"><em>Every country listed must be considered for cross-border notification to their IHR NFP if the case is confirmed.</em></p>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#5B21B6;font-weight:800;\">Clinical evidence</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:8px;\">\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;font-size:12px;\"><strong>Syndrome:</strong> VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER · <strong>triage:</strong> URGENT · <strong>ER signs:</strong> PRESENT</p>\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;font-size:13px;\">Symptoms PRESENT (6)</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 12px 18px;padding:0;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Bleeding gums or nose</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-21)</span> — Gums bled twice while brushing teeth</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Conjunctivitis</strong> — Bilateral scleral injection</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Continuous high-grade fever since arrival</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Retrosternal pain</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — Severe burning</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Severe fatigue</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Prostrate, unable to walk unassisted</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Very high fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — 39.4 °C at triage</li></ul><p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#047857;font-weight:600;font-size:13px;\">Explicitly ABSENT</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 4px 18px;padding:0;font-size:12px;\"><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Paralysis acute flaccid</li><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Rash vesicular pustular</li></ul>\n    <hr style=\"border:none;border-top:1px dashed #E2E8F0;margin:10px 0;\">\n    <ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#64748B;\">[UNKNOWN]</strong> Affected healthcare facility exposure — Visited local clinic in Goma for malaria test 5d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Close contact case — Relative died of haemorrhagic illness in Butembo 12d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Consumed bushmeat</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Contact with paralysis case</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Poultry or live bird exposure</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Travel from outbreak area — Returned from DRC North Kivu via Goma</li></ul>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#FEF3C7;border-left:4px solid #B45309;border-radius:6px;margin:12px 0;\">\n  <tr><td style=\"padding:14px 16px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;color:#92400E;font-weight:700;\">Disease intelligence</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:17px;font-weight:700;color:#0F172A;margin:4px 0 2px;\">Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#475569;margin-bottom:10px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div>\n    <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\">\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;\">Case fatality rate</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">50.0%</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;\">Incubation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">2–21 days (typically 4–10)</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">Transmission</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Direct contact with body fluids of symptomatic case or contaminated fomites; sexual transmission from survivors; bat reservoir</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">PPE</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">VHF full PPE: fluid-resistant coverall, double gloves, PAPR or N95+face shield, hood, boots, apron</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">Isolation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Dedicated VHF isolation ward / treatment centre with buddy-system PPE donning/doffing</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">IHR notification</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">IMMEDIATE — any suspected VHF is a public health event of potential international concern</td></tr>\n    </table>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:10px;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>WHO case definition:</strong> Acute fever ≥38°C and ≥3 of: headache, vomiting, anorexia, diarrhoea, lethargy, abdominal pain, muscle/joint pain, difficulty swallowing, difficulty breathing, hiccup, OR unexplained bleeding, OR contact with suspected/confirmed case within 21 days.</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Differential:</strong> Marburg, Lassa, CCHF, severe malaria, typhoid, meningococcaemia, severe dengue</div>\n  </td></tr>\n</table></td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:0 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#5B21B6;font-weight:800;\">Expected actions — NATIONAL IHR NFP</div>\n  <ol style=\"margin:10px 0 0 20px;padding:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\">Complete Annex 2 decision instrument within <strong>48 hours</strong>.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\">Coordinate multi-sectoral risk assessment (MoH + IHR NFP + PHEOC).</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\">If 2+ criteria confirmed → submit IHR notification to WHO within <strong>24 hours</strong>.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\">Pre-warn neighbouring country IHR NFPs if cross-border spread plausible.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\">Initiate appropriate border-health measures (screening, tracing, quarantine).</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:6px 0;\">Prepare public risk communication with WHO country office.</li>\n  </ol>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#5B21B6;font-weight:800;\">Current follow-up obligations (14)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F8FAFC;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#0369A1;\">[IN_PROGRESS]</strong> Case investigation started <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 13:30:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Index case isolated / treatment initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 22:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Close contacts identified and listed <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Contact tracing and follow-up operational <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Coordination structure activated (EOC / PHEOC) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> WHO and partners notified per IHR Article 6 <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory specimens collected and transported <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory confirmation obtained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Epidemiological line list maintained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Risk communication to the public initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Infection prevention &amp; control (IPC) in facilities <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Vector control measures (if applicable) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Cross-border / POE surveillance strengthened <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Response resources mobilised <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:20px 28px 14px;\">\n  <div style=\"background:#5B21B6;border-radius:8px;padding:14px 16px;text-align:center;\">\n    <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#FFFFFF;font-size:14px;font-weight:700;text-decoration:none;\">Complete Annex 2 assessment →</a>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:18px 28px 12px;background:#F1F5F9;border-top:1px solid #E2E8F0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:11px;color:#475569;line-height:1.5;\">\n    <strong>Uganda POE Sentinel</strong> · IHR ANNEX 2 ASSESSMENT · WHO IHR 2005 &amp; AFRO IDSR 3rd Ed. aligned.<br>\n    Alert <strong>DEMO_183022</strong> · CRITICAL — life-threatening · fired 30 minutes ago at 2026-04-21 18:00.<br>\n    Open in console → <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#1D4ED8;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;\">http://localhost/#/active-alerts</a>\n  </p>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:8px 28px 18px;background:#F1F5F9;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:10px;color:#64748B;line-height:1.4;\">\n    This is a transactional public-health alert generated by the national surveillance pipeline. Do not reply; coordinate through the escalation ladder.<br>\n    Generated 2026-04-21 18:30 UTC · template DEMO_183022 · recipient action expected within 4h.\n  </p>\n</td></tr></table></td></tr></table></body></html>', 'ALERT', 21, 'UG', 'KYOTERA', 'MUTUKULA', 'SENT', NULL, 0, '2026-04-21 18:30:48', NULL, NULL, 'CMD:demo-all', '2026-04-21 18:30:48', '2026-04-21 18:30:48'),
(237, 118, 'vexa256@gmail.com', NULL, 'EMAIL', 'ALERT_CASE_FILE', '🗂 CASE FILE · DEMO_183022 · A. O. · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · disposition ISOLATED', '\n  CASE FILE · dispatch to response partners\n  Traveller dispositioned — case file forwarded for continuity of care / contact tracing.\n  🗂 DEMO_183022 · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)\n  [CRITICAL] · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · POE MUTUKULA · Uganda · FEMALE · 34 y · syndrome: VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER · CFR 50.0%\n\n\n\n  This is the complete case dispatch package for receiving teams (DISTRICT + PHEOC + receiving hospital + contact tracers). It contains every field captured at MUTUKULA so you can receive,', '<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><meta charset=\"utf-8\"><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\"></head><body style=\"margin:0;padding:0;background:#EEF2F7;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;color:#0F172A;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#EEF2F7;padding:24px 12px;\"><tr><td align=\"center\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"640\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"max-width:640px;background:#FFFFFF;border-radius:10px;overflow:hidden;box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><tr><td style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,#134E4A 0%,#0F766E 55%,#14B8A6 100%);padding:24px 28px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#CCFBF1;font-weight:700;\">CASE FILE · dispatch to response partners</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#99F6E4;font-weight:600;\">Traveller dispositioned — case file forwarded for continuity of care / contact tracing.</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:10px;font-size:22px;font-weight:800;color:#FFFFFF;line-height:1.2;\">🗂 DEMO_183022 · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:13px;color:#CCFBF1;\">[CRITICAL] · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · POE MUTUKULA · Uganda · FEMALE · 34 y · syndrome: VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER · CFR 50.0%</div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:22px 28px 0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">This is the <strong>complete case dispatch package</strong> for receiving teams (DISTRICT + PHEOC + receiving hospital + contact tracers). It contains every field captured at MUTUKULA so you can receive, isolate, treat, investigate and trace without re-interviewing the traveller.</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">1 · IDENTIFICATION</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;background:#F0FDFA;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Name · Age · Gender · DOB</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">A. O. · 34 y · FEMALE</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Nationality</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">Uganda</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Occupation</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">Cross-border trader / market vendor</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Residence country</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">Uganda</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Contact · phone / email</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">+25••••••••19 · a***@example.org</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Emergency contact</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">Robert Okello (spouse) / +256751000111</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Destination in Uganda</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">KAMPALA · Mulago National Referral Hospital, Kampala</td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">2 · TRAVEL HISTORY</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;background:#F0FDFA;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Direction · purpose · stay</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">ENTRY · TRADE / commerce · sourcing goods · 14 days</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Journey start</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">DR Congo</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Embarkation port / city</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">Goma</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Conveyance · seat</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">LAND BUS-KBZ-2314 · seat 14B</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Arrival → departure</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">2026-04-21 12:30 → 2026-04-20 12:30</td></tr>\n  </table>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:10px 12px;background:#F0FDFA;border-left:3px solid #14B8A6;border-radius:4px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;color:#115E59;font-weight:700;\">Countries visited / transited</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:4px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>VISITED</strong> · DR Congo <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(2026-04-03 → 2026-04-19)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>TRANSIT</strong> · Rwanda <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(2026-04-19 → 2026-04-20)</span></li></ul></div>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">3 · CLINICAL FINDINGS</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;background:#F0FDFA;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Triage · general appearance</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">URGENT · UNWELL</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Emergency signs present</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">PRESENT</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Syndromic classification</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Assigned risk</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">CRITICAL</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Temperature</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;\">39.4 °C</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Pulse</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">112 bpm</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Respiratory rate</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;\">24 /min</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Blood pressure</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">98/60 mmHg</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">SpO₂</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">94 %</td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">4 · SYMPTOMS · 8</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F0FDFA;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;\"><p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;font-size:13px;\">Symptoms PRESENT (6)</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 12px 18px;padding:0;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Bleeding gums or nose</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-21)</span> — Gums bled twice while brushing teeth</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Conjunctivitis</strong> — Bilateral scleral injection</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Continuous high-grade fever since arrival</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Retrosternal pain</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — Severe burning</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Severe fatigue</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Prostrate, unable to walk unassisted</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Very high fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — 39.4 °C at triage</li></ul><p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#047857;font-weight:600;font-size:13px;\">Explicitly ABSENT</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 4px 18px;padding:0;font-size:12px;\"><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Paralysis acute flaccid</li><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Rash vesicular pustular</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">5 · EXPOSURES</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F0FDFA;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#64748B;\">[UNKNOWN]</strong> Affected healthcare facility exposure — Visited local clinic in Goma for malaria test 5d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Close contact case — Relative died of haemorrhagic illness in Butembo 12d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Consumed bushmeat</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Contact with paralysis case</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Poultry or live bird exposure</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Travel from outbreak area — Returned from DRC North Kivu via Goma</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">6 · DIFFERENTIAL · 4 ranked</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F0FDFA;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#1 · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 92% · 50.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Travel from North Kivu + haemorrhagic signs + contact with deceased case in Butembo</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#2 · Marburg Virus Disease (MVD)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 48% · 50.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Cannot exclude filovirus co-differential; fruit-bat exposure not confirmed</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#3 · Severe Malaria (P. falciparum)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 30% · 20.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">Endemic — CRITICAL</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Patient from DRC with fever — rule-out required before attributing bleeding to VHF</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#4 · Lassa fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 10% · 15.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">West-Africa travel absent but pharyngitis + retrosternal pain patterns similar</div></li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#FEF3C7;border-left:4px solid #B45309;border-radius:6px;margin:12px 0;\">\n  <tr><td style=\"padding:14px 16px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;color:#92400E;font-weight:700;\">Disease intelligence</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:17px;font-weight:700;color:#0F172A;margin:4px 0 2px;\">Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#475569;margin-bottom:10px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div>\n    <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\">\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;\">Case fatality rate</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">50.0%</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;\">Incubation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">2–21 days (typically 4–10)</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">Transmission</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Direct contact with body fluids of symptomatic case or contaminated fomites; sexual transmission from survivors; bat reservoir</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">PPE</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">VHF full PPE: fluid-resistant coverall, double gloves, PAPR or N95+face shield, hood, boots, apron</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">Isolation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Dedicated VHF isolation ward / treatment centre with buddy-system PPE donning/doffing</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">IHR notification</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">IMMEDIATE — any suspected VHF is a public health event of potential international concern</td></tr>\n    </table>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:10px;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>WHO case definition:</strong> Acute fever ≥38°C and ≥3 of: headache, vomiting, anorexia, diarrhoea, lethargy, abdominal pain, muscle/joint pain, difficulty swallowing, difficulty breathing, hiccup, OR unexplained bleeding, OR contact with suspected/confirmed case within 21 days.</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Differential:</strong> Marburg, Lassa, CCHF, severe malaria, typhoid, meningococcaemia, severe dengue</div>\n  </td></tr>\n</table></td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:0 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">7 · SAMPLES COLLECTED · 3</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F0FDFA;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">WHOLE_BLOOD_EDTA · ID: UVRI-183022-01 · → Uganda Virus Research Institute (UVRI), Entebbe · 2026-04-21 16:30:22</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">SERUM · ID: UVRI-183022-02 · → UVRI BSL-4 lab · 2026-04-21 16:30:22</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">ORAL_SWAB · ID: UVRI-183022-03 · → UVRI · 2026-04-21 16:30:22</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">8 · DISPOSITION &amp; OFFICER NOTES</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F0FDFA;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;\">\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;font-size:13px;\"><strong>Final disposition:</strong> ISOLATED</p>\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;font-size:13px;\"><strong>Detail:</strong> Transferred to Mulago VHF isolation ward under ambulance escort with full PPE team</p>\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;font-size:13px;\"><strong>Outcome:</strong> SUSPECT_CASE · <strong>follow-up:</strong> YES @ NATIONAL</p>\n    <p style=\"margin:10px 0 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Officer notes:</strong><br><em>Patient febrile with scleral injection and retrosternal pain. Reports contact with relative who died of unspecified haemorrhagic illness in Butembo 12 days ago. Isolated on arrival per VHF protocol. IV fluids in situ. Samples double-bagged pending UVRI courier. Recommend immediate ring-investigation of bus cohort (seats 13-15).</em></p>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">9 · ACTIONS TAKEN AT POE</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F0FDFA;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;list-style:none;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#047857;\">✓ AMBULANCE TRANSFER — Ambulance team briefed + escorted</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#B45309;\">○ CONTACT LINE LIST — Pending — bus cohort (seats 13–15) to be traced</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#047857;\">✓ ISOLATION — Isolated in dedicated VHF room on arrival</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#047857;\">✓ PPE DEPLOYED — Full VHF PPE for triage team</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#047857;\">✓ SAMPLE COLLECTION — Three specimens packaged per BSL-4 SOPs</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">10 · FOLLOW-UPS EXPECTED (14 · 1 overdue)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F0FDFA;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#0369A1;\">[IN_PROGRESS]</strong> Case investigation started <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 13:30:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Index case isolated / treatment initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 22:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Close contacts identified and listed <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Contact tracing and follow-up operational <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Coordination structure activated (EOC / PHEOC) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> WHO and partners notified per IHR Article 6 <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory specimens collected and transported <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory confirmation obtained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Epidemiological line list maintained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Risk communication to the public initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Infection prevention &amp; control (IPC) in facilities <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Vector control measures (if applicable) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Cross-border / POE surveillance strengthened <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Response resources mobilised <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">11 · CONTINUITY OF CARE · what receiving teams must do</div>\n  <ul style=\"margin:8px 0 0 20px;padding:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">\n    <li style=\"margin:5px 0;\">Re-verify identity on arrival using the initials/anonymous code above.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:5px 0;\">Maintain isolation posture per disease: <strong>Dedicated VHF isolation ward / treatment centre with buddy-system PPE donning/doffing</strong>. PPE: VHF full PPE: fluid-resistant coverall, double gloves, PAPR or N95+face shield, hood, boots, apron.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:5px 0;\">Collect any missing specimens: EDTA whole blood (5 mL), double-bagged, cold chain, dangerous-goods courier.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:5px 0;\">Initiate/continue the 14 seeded RTSL-14 follow-ups; blocks_closure flags matter.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:5px 0;\">Trace contacts per disease incubation window: 2–21 days (typically 4–10).</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:5px 0;\">Notify NATIONAL + national IHR NFP per: IMMEDIATE — any suspected VHF is a public health event of potential international concern.</li>\n  </ul>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:20px 28px 14px;\">\n  <div style=\"background:#0F766E;border-radius:8px;padding:14px 16px;text-align:center;\">\n    <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#FFFFFF;font-size:14px;font-weight:700;text-decoration:none;\">Open full case file in console →</a>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:18px 28px 12px;background:#F1F5F9;border-top:1px solid #E2E8F0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:11px;color:#475569;line-height:1.5;\">\n    <strong>Uganda POE Sentinel</strong> · CASE-FILE DISPATCH · WHO IHR 2005 &amp; AFRO IDSR 3rd Ed. aligned.<br>\n    Alert <strong>DEMO_183022</strong> · CRITICAL — life-threatening · fired 30 minutes ago at 2026-04-21 18:00.<br>\n    Open in console → <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#1D4ED8;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;\">http://localhost/#/active-alerts</a>\n  </p>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:8px 28px 18px;background:#F1F5F9;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:10px;color:#64748B;line-height:1.4;\">\n    This is a transactional public-health alert generated by the national surveillance pipeline. Do not reply; coordinate through the escalation ladder.<br>\n    Generated 2026-04-21 18:30 UTC · template DEMO_183022 · recipient action expected within 4h.\n  </p>\n</td></tr></table></td></tr></table></body></html>', 'ALERT', 21, 'UG', 'KYOTERA', 'MUTUKULA', 'SENT', NULL, 0, '2026-04-21 18:30:49', NULL, NULL, 'CMD:demo-all', '2026-04-21 18:30:49', '2026-04-21 18:30:49');
INSERT INTO `notification_log` (`id`, `contact_id`, `to_email`, `to_phone`, `channel`, `template_code`, `subject`, `body_preview`, `body_full`, `related_entity_type`, `related_entity_id`, `country_code`, `district_code`, `poe_code`, `status`, `error_message`, `retry_count`, `sent_at`, `delivered_at`, `failed_at`, `triggered_by`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(238, 54, 'ayebare.k.timothy@gmail.com', NULL, 'EMAIL', 'ALERT_CASE_FILE', '🗂 CASE FILE · DEMO_183022 · A. O. · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · disposition ISOLATED', '\n  CASE FILE · dispatch to response partners\n  Traveller dispositioned — case file forwarded for continuity of care / contact tracing.\n  🗂 DEMO_183022 · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)\n  [CRITICAL] · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · POE MUTUKULA · Uganda · FEMALE · 34 y · syndrome: VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER · CFR 50.0%\n\n\n\n  This is the complete case dispatch package for receiving teams (DISTRICT + PHEOC + receiving hospital + contact tracers). It contains every field captured at MUTUKULA so you can receive,', '<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><meta charset=\"utf-8\"><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\"></head><body style=\"margin:0;padding:0;background:#EEF2F7;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;color:#0F172A;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#EEF2F7;padding:24px 12px;\"><tr><td align=\"center\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"640\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"max-width:640px;background:#FFFFFF;border-radius:10px;overflow:hidden;box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><tr><td style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,#134E4A 0%,#0F766E 55%,#14B8A6 100%);padding:24px 28px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#CCFBF1;font-weight:700;\">CASE FILE · dispatch to response partners</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#99F6E4;font-weight:600;\">Traveller dispositioned — case file forwarded for continuity of care / contact tracing.</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:10px;font-size:22px;font-weight:800;color:#FFFFFF;line-height:1.2;\">🗂 DEMO_183022 · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:13px;color:#CCFBF1;\">[CRITICAL] · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · POE MUTUKULA · Uganda · FEMALE · 34 y · syndrome: VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER · CFR 50.0%</div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:22px 28px 0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">This is the <strong>complete case dispatch package</strong> for receiving teams (DISTRICT + PHEOC + receiving hospital + contact tracers). It contains every field captured at MUTUKULA so you can receive, isolate, treat, investigate and trace without re-interviewing the traveller.</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">1 · IDENTIFICATION</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;background:#F0FDFA;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Name · Age · Gender · DOB</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">A. O. · 34 y · FEMALE</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Nationality</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">Uganda</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Occupation</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">Cross-border trader / market vendor</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Residence country</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">Uganda</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Contact · phone / email</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">+25••••••••19 · a***@example.org</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Emergency contact</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">Robert Okello (spouse) / +256751000111</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Destination in Uganda</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">KAMPALA · Mulago National Referral Hospital, Kampala</td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">2 · TRAVEL HISTORY</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;background:#F0FDFA;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Direction · purpose · stay</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">ENTRY · TRADE / commerce · sourcing goods · 14 days</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Journey start</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">DR Congo</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Embarkation port / city</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">Goma</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Conveyance · seat</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">LAND BUS-KBZ-2314 · seat 14B</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Arrival → departure</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">2026-04-21 12:30 → 2026-04-20 12:30</td></tr>\n  </table>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:10px 12px;background:#F0FDFA;border-left:3px solid #14B8A6;border-radius:4px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;color:#115E59;font-weight:700;\">Countries visited / transited</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:4px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>VISITED</strong> · DR Congo <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(2026-04-03 → 2026-04-19)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>TRANSIT</strong> · Rwanda <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(2026-04-19 → 2026-04-20)</span></li></ul></div>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">3 · CLINICAL FINDINGS</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;background:#F0FDFA;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Triage · general appearance</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">URGENT · UNWELL</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Emergency signs present</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">PRESENT</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Syndromic classification</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Assigned risk</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">CRITICAL</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Temperature</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;\">39.4 °C</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Pulse</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">112 bpm</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Respiratory rate</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;\">24 /min</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Blood pressure</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">98/60 mmHg</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">SpO₂</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">94 %</td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">4 · SYMPTOMS · 8</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F0FDFA;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;\"><p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;font-size:13px;\">Symptoms PRESENT (6)</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 12px 18px;padding:0;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Bleeding gums or nose</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-21)</span> — Gums bled twice while brushing teeth</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Conjunctivitis</strong> — Bilateral scleral injection</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Continuous high-grade fever since arrival</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Retrosternal pain</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — Severe burning</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Severe fatigue</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Prostrate, unable to walk unassisted</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Very high fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — 39.4 °C at triage</li></ul><p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#047857;font-weight:600;font-size:13px;\">Explicitly ABSENT</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 4px 18px;padding:0;font-size:12px;\"><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Paralysis acute flaccid</li><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Rash vesicular pustular</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">5 · EXPOSURES</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F0FDFA;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#64748B;\">[UNKNOWN]</strong> Affected healthcare facility exposure — Visited local clinic in Goma for malaria test 5d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Close contact case — Relative died of haemorrhagic illness in Butembo 12d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Consumed bushmeat</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Contact with paralysis case</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Poultry or live bird exposure</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Travel from outbreak area — Returned from DRC North Kivu via Goma</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">6 · DIFFERENTIAL · 4 ranked</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F0FDFA;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#1 · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 92% · 50.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Travel from North Kivu + haemorrhagic signs + contact with deceased case in Butembo</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#2 · Marburg Virus Disease (MVD)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 48% · 50.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Cannot exclude filovirus co-differential; fruit-bat exposure not confirmed</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#3 · Severe Malaria (P. falciparum)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 30% · 20.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">Endemic — CRITICAL</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Patient from DRC with fever — rule-out required before attributing bleeding to VHF</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#4 · Lassa fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 10% · 15.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">West-Africa travel absent but pharyngitis + retrosternal pain patterns similar</div></li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#FEF3C7;border-left:4px solid #B45309;border-radius:6px;margin:12px 0;\">\n  <tr><td style=\"padding:14px 16px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;color:#92400E;font-weight:700;\">Disease intelligence</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:17px;font-weight:700;color:#0F172A;margin:4px 0 2px;\">Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#475569;margin-bottom:10px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div>\n    <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\">\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;\">Case fatality rate</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">50.0%</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;\">Incubation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">2–21 days (typically 4–10)</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">Transmission</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Direct contact with body fluids of symptomatic case or contaminated fomites; sexual transmission from survivors; bat reservoir</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">PPE</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">VHF full PPE: fluid-resistant coverall, double gloves, PAPR or N95+face shield, hood, boots, apron</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">Isolation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Dedicated VHF isolation ward / treatment centre with buddy-system PPE donning/doffing</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">IHR notification</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">IMMEDIATE — any suspected VHF is a public health event of potential international concern</td></tr>\n    </table>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:10px;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>WHO case definition:</strong> Acute fever ≥38°C and ≥3 of: headache, vomiting, anorexia, diarrhoea, lethargy, abdominal pain, muscle/joint pain, difficulty swallowing, difficulty breathing, hiccup, OR unexplained bleeding, OR contact with suspected/confirmed case within 21 days.</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Differential:</strong> Marburg, Lassa, CCHF, severe malaria, typhoid, meningococcaemia, severe dengue</div>\n  </td></tr>\n</table></td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:0 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">7 · SAMPLES COLLECTED · 3</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F0FDFA;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">WHOLE_BLOOD_EDTA · ID: UVRI-183022-01 · → Uganda Virus Research Institute (UVRI), Entebbe · 2026-04-21 16:30:22</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">SERUM · ID: UVRI-183022-02 · → UVRI BSL-4 lab · 2026-04-21 16:30:22</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">ORAL_SWAB · ID: UVRI-183022-03 · → UVRI · 2026-04-21 16:30:22</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">8 · DISPOSITION &amp; OFFICER NOTES</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F0FDFA;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;\">\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;font-size:13px;\"><strong>Final disposition:</strong> ISOLATED</p>\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;font-size:13px;\"><strong>Detail:</strong> Transferred to Mulago VHF isolation ward under ambulance escort with full PPE team</p>\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;font-size:13px;\"><strong>Outcome:</strong> SUSPECT_CASE · <strong>follow-up:</strong> YES @ NATIONAL</p>\n    <p style=\"margin:10px 0 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Officer notes:</strong><br><em>Patient febrile with scleral injection and retrosternal pain. Reports contact with relative who died of unspecified haemorrhagic illness in Butembo 12 days ago. Isolated on arrival per VHF protocol. IV fluids in situ. Samples double-bagged pending UVRI courier. Recommend immediate ring-investigation of bus cohort (seats 13-15).</em></p>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">9 · ACTIONS TAKEN AT POE</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F0FDFA;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;list-style:none;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#047857;\">✓ AMBULANCE TRANSFER — Ambulance team briefed + escorted</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#B45309;\">○ CONTACT LINE LIST — Pending — bus cohort (seats 13–15) to be traced</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#047857;\">✓ ISOLATION — Isolated in dedicated VHF room on arrival</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#047857;\">✓ PPE DEPLOYED — Full VHF PPE for triage team</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#047857;\">✓ SAMPLE COLLECTION — Three specimens packaged per BSL-4 SOPs</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">10 · FOLLOW-UPS EXPECTED (14 · 1 overdue)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F0FDFA;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#0369A1;\">[IN_PROGRESS]</strong> Case investigation started <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 13:30:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Index case isolated / treatment initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 22:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Close contacts identified and listed <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Contact tracing and follow-up operational <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Coordination structure activated (EOC / PHEOC) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> WHO and partners notified per IHR Article 6 <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory specimens collected and transported <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory confirmation obtained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Epidemiological line list maintained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Risk communication to the public initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Infection prevention &amp; control (IPC) in facilities <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Vector control measures (if applicable) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Cross-border / POE surveillance strengthened <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Response resources mobilised <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">11 · CONTINUITY OF CARE · what receiving teams must do</div>\n  <ul style=\"margin:8px 0 0 20px;padding:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">\n    <li style=\"margin:5px 0;\">Re-verify identity on arrival using the initials/anonymous code above.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:5px 0;\">Maintain isolation posture per disease: <strong>Dedicated VHF isolation ward / treatment centre with buddy-system PPE donning/doffing</strong>. PPE: VHF full PPE: fluid-resistant coverall, double gloves, PAPR or N95+face shield, hood, boots, apron.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:5px 0;\">Collect any missing specimens: EDTA whole blood (5 mL), double-bagged, cold chain, dangerous-goods courier.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:5px 0;\">Initiate/continue the 14 seeded RTSL-14 follow-ups; blocks_closure flags matter.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:5px 0;\">Trace contacts per disease incubation window: 2–21 days (typically 4–10).</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:5px 0;\">Notify NATIONAL + national IHR NFP per: IMMEDIATE — any suspected VHF is a public health event of potential international concern.</li>\n  </ul>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:20px 28px 14px;\">\n  <div style=\"background:#0F766E;border-radius:8px;padding:14px 16px;text-align:center;\">\n    <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#FFFFFF;font-size:14px;font-weight:700;text-decoration:none;\">Open full case file in console →</a>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:18px 28px 12px;background:#F1F5F9;border-top:1px solid #E2E8F0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:11px;color:#475569;line-height:1.5;\">\n    <strong>Uganda POE Sentinel</strong> · CASE-FILE DISPATCH · WHO IHR 2005 &amp; AFRO IDSR 3rd Ed. aligned.<br>\n    Alert <strong>DEMO_183022</strong> · CRITICAL — life-threatening · fired 30 minutes ago at 2026-04-21 18:00.<br>\n    Open in console → <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#1D4ED8;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;\">http://localhost/#/active-alerts</a>\n  </p>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:8px 28px 18px;background:#F1F5F9;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:10px;color:#64748B;line-height:1.4;\">\n    This is a transactional public-health alert generated by the national surveillance pipeline. Do not reply; coordinate through the escalation ladder.<br>\n    Generated 2026-04-21 18:30 UTC · template DEMO_183022 · recipient action expected within 4h.\n  </p>\n</td></tr></table></td></tr></table></body></html>', 'ALERT', 21, 'UG', 'KYOTERA', 'MUTUKULA', 'SENT', NULL, 0, '2026-04-21 18:30:51', NULL, NULL, 'CMD:demo-all', '2026-04-21 18:30:51', '2026-04-21 18:30:51'),
(239, 119, 'ecsahccloudsurveillancealerts@gmail.com', NULL, 'EMAIL', 'ALERT_CASE_FILE', '🗂 CASE FILE · DEMO_183022 · A. O. · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · disposition ISOLATED', '\n  CASE FILE · dispatch to response partners\n  Traveller dispositioned — case file forwarded for continuity of care / contact tracing.\n  🗂 DEMO_183022 · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)\n  [CRITICAL] · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · POE MUTUKULA · Uganda · FEMALE · 34 y · syndrome: VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER · CFR 50.0%\n\n\n\n  This is the complete case dispatch package for receiving teams (DISTRICT + PHEOC + receiving hospital + contact tracers). It contains every field captured at MUTUKULA so you can receive,', '<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><meta charset=\"utf-8\"><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\"></head><body style=\"margin:0;padding:0;background:#EEF2F7;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;color:#0F172A;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#EEF2F7;padding:24px 12px;\"><tr><td align=\"center\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"640\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"max-width:640px;background:#FFFFFF;border-radius:10px;overflow:hidden;box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><tr><td style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,#134E4A 0%,#0F766E 55%,#14B8A6 100%);padding:24px 28px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#CCFBF1;font-weight:700;\">CASE FILE · dispatch to response partners</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#99F6E4;font-weight:600;\">Traveller dispositioned — case file forwarded for continuity of care / contact tracing.</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:10px;font-size:22px;font-weight:800;color:#FFFFFF;line-height:1.2;\">🗂 DEMO_183022 · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:13px;color:#CCFBF1;\">[CRITICAL] · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · POE MUTUKULA · Uganda · FEMALE · 34 y · syndrome: VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER · CFR 50.0%</div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:22px 28px 0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">This is the <strong>complete case dispatch package</strong> for receiving teams (DISTRICT + PHEOC + receiving hospital + contact tracers). It contains every field captured at MUTUKULA so you can receive, isolate, treat, investigate and trace without re-interviewing the traveller.</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">1 · IDENTIFICATION</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;background:#F0FDFA;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Name · Age · Gender · DOB</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">A. O. · 34 y · FEMALE</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Nationality</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">Uganda</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Occupation</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">Cross-border trader / market vendor</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Residence country</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">Uganda</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Contact · phone / email</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">+25••••••••19 · a***@example.org</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Emergency contact</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">Robert Okello (spouse) / +256751000111</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Destination in Uganda</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">KAMPALA · Mulago National Referral Hospital, Kampala</td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">2 · TRAVEL HISTORY</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;background:#F0FDFA;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Direction · purpose · stay</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">ENTRY · TRADE / commerce · sourcing goods · 14 days</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Journey start</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">DR Congo</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Embarkation port / city</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">Goma</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Conveyance · seat</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">LAND BUS-KBZ-2314 · seat 14B</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Arrival → departure</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">2026-04-21 12:30 → 2026-04-20 12:30</td></tr>\n  </table>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:10px 12px;background:#F0FDFA;border-left:3px solid #14B8A6;border-radius:4px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;color:#115E59;font-weight:700;\">Countries visited / transited</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:4px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>VISITED</strong> · DR Congo <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(2026-04-03 → 2026-04-19)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>TRANSIT</strong> · Rwanda <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(2026-04-19 → 2026-04-20)</span></li></ul></div>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">3 · CLINICAL FINDINGS</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;background:#F0FDFA;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Triage · general appearance</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">URGENT · UNWELL</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Emergency signs present</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">PRESENT</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Syndromic classification</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#115E59;\">Assigned risk</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">CRITICAL</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Temperature</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;\">39.4 °C</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Pulse</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">112 bpm</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Respiratory rate</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;\">24 /min</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">Blood pressure</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">98/60 mmHg</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;color:#475569;font-size:13px;\">SpO₂</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:13px;text-align:right;color:#0F172A;font-weight:600;\">94 %</td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">4 · SYMPTOMS · 8</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F0FDFA;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;\"><p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:700;font-size:13px;\">Symptoms PRESENT (6)</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 12px 18px;padding:0;font-size:13px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Bleeding gums or nose</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-21)</span> — Gums bled twice while brushing teeth</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Conjunctivitis</strong> — Bilateral scleral injection</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Continuous high-grade fever since arrival</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Retrosternal pain</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — Severe burning</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Severe fatigue</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-18)</span> — Prostrate, unable to walk unassisted</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Very high fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(onset 2026-04-19)</span> — 39.4 °C at triage</li></ul><p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#047857;font-weight:600;font-size:13px;\">Explicitly ABSENT</p><ul style=\"margin:0 0 4px 18px;padding:0;font-size:12px;\"><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Paralysis acute flaccid</li><li style=\"margin:2px 0;color:#475569;\">Rash vesicular pustular</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">5 · EXPOSURES</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F0FDFA;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#64748B;\">[UNKNOWN]</strong> Affected healthcare facility exposure — Visited local clinic in Goma for malaria test 5d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Close contact case — Relative died of haemorrhagic illness in Butembo 12d ago</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Consumed bushmeat</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Contact with paralysis case</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#047857;\">[NO]</strong> Poultry or live bird exposure</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B91C1C;\">[YES]</strong> Travel from outbreak area — Returned from DRC North Kivu via Goma</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">6 · DIFFERENTIAL · 4 ranked</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F0FDFA;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#1 · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 92% · 50.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Travel from North Kivu + haemorrhagic signs + contact with deceased case in Butembo</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#2 · Marburg Virus Disease (MVD)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 48% · 50.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Cannot exclude filovirus co-differential; fruit-bat exposure not confirmed</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#3 · Severe Malaria (P. falciparum)</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 30% · 20.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">Endemic — CRITICAL</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">Patient from DRC with fever — rule-out required before attributing bleeding to VHF</div></li><li style=\"margin:6px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong>#4 · Lassa fever</strong> <span style=\"color:#475569;\">· confidence 10% · 15.0% CFR</span><div style=\"color:#64748B;font-size:11px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div><div style=\"color:#475569;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px;\">West-Africa travel absent but pharyngitis + retrosternal pain patterns similar</div></li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#FEF3C7;border-left:4px solid #B45309;border-radius:6px;margin:12px 0;\">\n  <tr><td style=\"padding:14px 16px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;color:#92400E;font-weight:700;\">Disease intelligence</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:17px;font-weight:700;color:#0F172A;margin:4px 0 2px;\">Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#475569;margin-bottom:10px;\">IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</div>\n    <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\">\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;\">Case fatality rate</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">50.0%</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;\">Incubation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">2–21 days (typically 4–10)</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">Transmission</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Direct contact with body fluids of symptomatic case or contaminated fomites; sexual transmission from survivors; bat reservoir</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">PPE</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">VHF full PPE: fluid-resistant coverall, double gloves, PAPR or N95+face shield, hood, boots, apron</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">Isolation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Dedicated VHF isolation ward / treatment centre with buddy-system PPE donning/doffing</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">IHR notification</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">IMMEDIATE — any suspected VHF is a public health event of potential international concern</td></tr>\n    </table>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:10px;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>WHO case definition:</strong> Acute fever ≥38°C and ≥3 of: headache, vomiting, anorexia, diarrhoea, lethargy, abdominal pain, muscle/joint pain, difficulty swallowing, difficulty breathing, hiccup, OR unexplained bleeding, OR contact with suspected/confirmed case within 21 days.</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Differential:</strong> Marburg, Lassa, CCHF, severe malaria, typhoid, meningococcaemia, severe dengue</div>\n  </td></tr>\n</table></td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:0 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">7 · SAMPLES COLLECTED · 3</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F0FDFA;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">WHOLE_BLOOD_EDTA · ID: UVRI-183022-01 · → Uganda Virus Research Institute (UVRI), Entebbe · 2026-04-21 16:30:22</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">SERUM · ID: UVRI-183022-02 · → UVRI BSL-4 lab · 2026-04-21 16:30:22</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">ORAL_SWAB · ID: UVRI-183022-03 · → UVRI · 2026-04-21 16:30:22</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">8 · DISPOSITION &amp; OFFICER NOTES</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F0FDFA;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;\">\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;font-size:13px;\"><strong>Final disposition:</strong> ISOLATED</p>\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;font-size:13px;\"><strong>Detail:</strong> Transferred to Mulago VHF isolation ward under ambulance escort with full PPE team</p>\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 6px;font-size:13px;\"><strong>Outcome:</strong> SUSPECT_CASE · <strong>follow-up:</strong> YES @ NATIONAL</p>\n    <p style=\"margin:10px 0 0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Officer notes:</strong><br><em>Patient febrile with scleral injection and retrosternal pain. Reports contact with relative who died of unspecified haemorrhagic illness in Butembo 12 days ago. Isolated on arrival per VHF protocol. IV fluids in situ. Samples double-bagged pending UVRI courier. Recommend immediate ring-investigation of bus cohort (seats 13-15).</em></p>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">9 · ACTIONS TAKEN AT POE</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F0FDFA;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;list-style:none;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#047857;\">✓ AMBULANCE TRANSFER — Ambulance team briefed + escorted</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#B45309;\">○ CONTACT LINE LIST — Pending — bus cohort (seats 13–15) to be traced</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#047857;\">✓ ISOLATION — Isolated in dedicated VHF room on arrival</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#047857;\">✓ PPE DEPLOYED — Full VHF PPE for triage team</li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;color:#047857;\">✓ SAMPLE COLLECTION — Three specimens packaged per BSL-4 SOPs</li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">10 · FOLLOW-UPS EXPECTED (14 · 1 overdue)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#F0FDFA;border:1px solid #CCFBF1;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#0369A1;\">[IN_PROGRESS]</strong> Case investigation started <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 13:30:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Index case isolated / treatment initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 22:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Close contacts identified and listed <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Contact tracing and follow-up operational <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Coordination structure activated (EOC / PHEOC) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> WHO and partners notified per IHR Article 6 <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory specimens collected and transported <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory confirmation obtained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Epidemiological line list maintained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Risk communication to the public initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Infection prevention &amp; control (IPC) in facilities <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Vector control measures (if applicable) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Cross-border / POE surveillance strengthened <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Response resources mobilised <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0F766E;font-weight:800;\">11 · CONTINUITY OF CARE · what receiving teams must do</div>\n  <ul style=\"margin:8px 0 0 20px;padding:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">\n    <li style=\"margin:5px 0;\">Re-verify identity on arrival using the initials/anonymous code above.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:5px 0;\">Maintain isolation posture per disease: <strong>Dedicated VHF isolation ward / treatment centre with buddy-system PPE donning/doffing</strong>. PPE: VHF full PPE: fluid-resistant coverall, double gloves, PAPR or N95+face shield, hood, boots, apron.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:5px 0;\">Collect any missing specimens: EDTA whole blood (5 mL), double-bagged, cold chain, dangerous-goods courier.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:5px 0;\">Initiate/continue the 14 seeded RTSL-14 follow-ups; blocks_closure flags matter.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:5px 0;\">Trace contacts per disease incubation window: 2–21 days (typically 4–10).</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:5px 0;\">Notify NATIONAL + national IHR NFP per: IMMEDIATE — any suspected VHF is a public health event of potential international concern.</li>\n  </ul>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:20px 28px 14px;\">\n  <div style=\"background:#0F766E;border-radius:8px;padding:14px 16px;text-align:center;\">\n    <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#FFFFFF;font-size:14px;font-weight:700;text-decoration:none;\">Open full case file in console →</a>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:18px 28px 12px;background:#F1F5F9;border-top:1px solid #E2E8F0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:11px;color:#475569;line-height:1.5;\">\n    <strong>Uganda POE Sentinel</strong> · CASE-FILE DISPATCH · WHO IHR 2005 &amp; AFRO IDSR 3rd Ed. aligned.<br>\n    Alert <strong>DEMO_183022</strong> · CRITICAL — life-threatening · fired 30 minutes ago at 2026-04-21 18:00.<br>\n    Open in console → <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#1D4ED8;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;\">http://localhost/#/active-alerts</a>\n  </p>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:8px 28px 18px;background:#F1F5F9;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:10px;color:#64748B;line-height:1.4;\">\n    This is a transactional public-health alert generated by the national surveillance pipeline. Do not reply; coordinate through the escalation ladder.<br>\n    Generated 2026-04-21 18:30 UTC · template DEMO_183022 · recipient action expected within 4h.\n  </p>\n</td></tr></table></td></tr></table></body></html>', 'ALERT', 21, 'UG', 'KYOTERA', 'MUTUKULA', 'SENT', NULL, 0, '2026-04-21 18:30:53', NULL, NULL, 'CMD:demo-all', '2026-04-21 18:30:53', '2026-04-21 18:30:53');
