s (typically 4–10)</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">Transmission</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Direct contact with body fluids of symptomatic case or contaminated fomites; sexual transmission from survivors; bat reservoir</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">PPE</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">VHF full PPE: fluid-resistant coverall, double gloves, PAPR or N95+face shield, hood, boots, apron</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">Isolation</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">Dedicated VHF isolation ward / treatment centre with buddy-system PPE donning/doffing</td></tr>\n      <tr><td style=\"padding:3px 0;color:#64748B;vertical-align:top;\">IHR notification</td><td style=\"padding:3px 0;text-align:right;\">IMMEDIATE — any suspected VHF is a public health event of potential international concern</td></tr>\n    </table>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:10px;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>WHO case definition:</strong> Acute fever ≥38°C and ≥3 of: headache, vomiting, anorexia, diarrhoea, lethargy, abdominal pain, muscle/joint pain, difficulty swallowing, difficulty breathing, hiccup, OR unexplained bleeding, OR contact with suspected/confirmed case within 21 days.</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\"><strong>Differential:</strong> Marburg, Lassa, CCHF, severe malaria, typhoid, meningococcaemia, severe dengue</div>\n  </td></tr>\n</table></td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:0 28px 14px;\">\n  <div style=\"background:#BE123C;border-radius:8px;padding:14px 16px;text-align:center;\">\n    <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#FFFFFF;font-size:14px;font-weight:700;text-decoration:none;\">Take command of DEMO_183022 →</a>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:18px 28px 12px;background:#F1F5F9;border-top:1px solid #E2E8F0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:11px;color:#475569;line-height:1.5;\">\n    <strong>Uganda POE Sentinel</strong> · ESCALATION NOTICE · WHO IHR 2005 &amp; AFRO IDSR 3rd Ed. aligned.<br>\n    Alert <strong>DEMO_183022</strong> · CRITICAL — life-threatening · fired 30 minutes ago at 2026-04-21 18:00.<br>\n    Open in console → <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#1D4ED8;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;\">http://localhost/#/active-alerts</a>\n  </p>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:8px 28px 18px;background:#F1F5F9;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:10px;color:#64748B;line-height:1.4;\">\n    This is a transactional public-health alert generated by the national surveillance pipeline. Do not reply; coordinate through the escalation ladder.<br>\n    Generated 2026-04-21 18:30 UTC · template DEMO_183022 · recipient action expected within 4h.\n  </p>\n</td></tr></table></td></tr></table></body></html>', 'ALERT', 21, 'UG', 'KYOTERA', 'MUTUKULA', 'SENT', NULL, 0, '2026-04-21 18:31:02', NULL, NULL, 'CMD:demo-all', '2026-04-21 18:31:02', '2026-04-21 18:31:02'),
(245, 119, 'ecsahccloudsurveillancealerts@gmail.com', NULL, 'EMAIL', 'ESCALATION', '▲ ESCALATION · DEMO_183022 · to NATIONAL · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)', '\n  ESCALATION · next level of command\n  This alert could not be resolved at the previous level and is being escalated.\n  ▲ DEMO_183022 escalated to NATIONAL\n  Suspected VHF — returned traveller from DRC North Kivu\n\n\n\n  You are receiving this because DEMO_183022 requires decision-making capacity that does not sit at the POE or district level. Below is the rationale, the history so far, and the exact decisions expected of you.\n\n\n\n  Why this is being escalated\n  \n    Risk classification: CRITICAL —', '<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><meta charset=\"utf-8\"><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\"></head><body style=\"margin:0;padding:0;background:#EEF2F7;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;color:#0F172A;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#EEF2F7;padding:24px 12px;\"><tr><td align=\"center\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"640\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"max-width:640px;background:#FFFFFF;border-radius:10px;overflow:hidden;box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><tr><td style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,#881337 0%,#BE123C 55%,#E11D48 100%);padding:26px 28px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#FECDD3;font-weight:700;\">ESCALATION · next level of command</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#FECDD3;font-weight:600;\">This alert could not be resolved at the previous level and is being escalated.</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:12px;font-size:22px;font-weight:800;color:#FFFFFF;line-height:1.15;\">▲ DEMO_183022 escalated to NATIONAL</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;font-size:13px;color:#FECDD3;\">Suspected VHF — returned traveller from DRC North Kivu</div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:22px 28px 0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">You are receiving this because DEMO_183022 requires decision-making capacity that does not sit at the POE or district level. Below is the rationale, the history so far, and the exact decisions expected of you.</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#BE123C;font-weight:800;\">Why this is being escalated</div>\n  <ul style=\"margin:8px 0 0 20px;padding:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">\n    <li style=\"margin:4px 0;\">Risk classification: <strong>CRITICAL — life-threatening</strong>.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:4px 0;\">Suspected disease: <strong>Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</strong> (IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)) — CFR 50.0%.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:4px 0;\">IHR notification window: IMMEDIATE — any suspected VHF is a public health event of potential international concern.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:4px 0;\">1 of 14 follow-up actions are already overdue.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:4px 0;\">Escalation ladder in effect: NATIONAL → WHO IHR NFP.</li>\n  </ul>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#BE123C;font-weight:800;\">Decisions expected of you</div>\n  <ol style=\"margin:8px 0 0 20px;padding:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">\n    <li style=\"margin:5px 0;\">Acknowledge the alert in the console within <strong>4 hours</strong> (by 2026-04-21 22:00).</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:5px 0;\">Reassign owners for the 1 overdue follow-ups.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:5px 0;\">Authorise escalation to the next ladder level if appropriate.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:5px 0;\">Confirm isolation posture per disease: Dedicated VHF isolation ward / treatment centre with buddy-system PPE donning/doffing.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:5px 0;\">Coordinate with WHO country office if the Annex 2 criteria warrant notification.</li>\n  </ol>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#BE123C;font-weight:800;\">Snapshot of case</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;background:#F8FAFC;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Traveller</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">A. O. · 34 y · Uganda</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">POE · district</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">MUTUKULA · KYOTERA · Uganda</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Syndrome · triage</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER · URGENT</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Disposition</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">ISOLATED (Transferred to Mulago VHF isolation ward under ambulance escort with full PPE team)</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Officer notes</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\"><em>Patient febrile with scleral injection and retrosternal pain. Reports contact with relative who died of unspecified haemorrhagic illness in Butembo 12 days ago. Isolated on arrival per VHF protocol. IV fluids in situ. Samples double-bagged pending UVRI courier. Recommend immediate ring-investigation of bus cohort (seats 13-15).</em></td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#BE123C;font-weight:800;\">Outstanding follow-ups (1 overdue)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#FFF1F2;border:1px solid #FECDD3;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#0369A1;\">[IN_PROGRESS]</strong> Case investigation started <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 13:30:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Index case isolated / treatment initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 22:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Close contacts identified and listed <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Contact tracing and follow-up operational <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Coordination structure activated (EOC / PHEOC) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> WHO and partners notified per IHR Article 6 <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory specimens collected and transported <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory confirmation obtained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Epidemiological line list maintained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"colo