16px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">What happens if this stays overdue</div>\n  <ul style=\"margin:8px 0 0 20px;padding:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">\n    <li style=\"margin:4px 0;\">7-1-7 response window is being eaten — this <em>will</em> cause a BREACH_717 notice.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:4px 0;\">If <strong>blocks_closure = YES</strong> the parent alert cannot be closed until this is resolved.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:4px 0;\">On next digest the alert is flagged on the national intelligence brief.</li>\n    <li style=\"margin:4px 0;\">Supervisor level (NATIONAL) is now receiving these notices until resolution.</li>\n  </ul>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">Case in which this action sits</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;background:#F8FAFC;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Alert · risk</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">DEMO_183022 · CRITICAL — life-threatening</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Disease</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">Ebola Virus Disease (EVD)</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Country · POE · district</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">Uganda · MUTUKULA · KYOTERA</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Disposition</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">ISOLATED</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Officer notes</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\"><em>Patient febrile with scleral injection and retrosternal pain. Reports contact with relative who died of unspecified haemorrhagic illness in Butembo 12 days ago. Isolated on arrival per VHF protocol. IV fluids in situ. Samples double-bagged pending UVRI courier. Recommend immediate ring-investigation of bus cohort (seats 13-15).</em></td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B91C1C;font-weight:800;\">Other follow-ups (14 · 1 overdue)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#FFF1F2;border:1px solid #FECDD3;border-radius:6px;\"><ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;\"><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#0369A1;\">[IN_PROGRESS]</strong> Case investigation started <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 13:30:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Index case isolated / treatment initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-21 22:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Close contacts identified and listed <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Contact tracing and follow-up operational <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Coordination structure activated (EOC / PHEOC) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> WHO and partners notified per IHR Article 6 <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-22 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory specimens collected and transported <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Laboratory confirmation obtained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Epidemiological line list maintained <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-23 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Risk communication to the public initiated <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Infection prevention &amp; control (IPC) in facilities <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Vector control measures (if applicable) <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-24 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Cross-border / POE surveillance strengthened <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li><li style=\"margin:4px 0;font-size:13px;\"><strong style=\"color:#B45309;\">[PENDING]</strong> Response resources mobilised <span style=\"color:#64748B;\">(due 2026-04-28 18:00:22)</span></li></ul></div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:20px 28px 14px;\">\n  <div style=\"background:#B91C1C;border-radius:8px;padding:14px 16px;text-align:center;\">\n    <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#FFFFFF;font-size:14px;font-weight:700;text-decoration:none;\">Resolve CASE_INVESTIGATION now →</a>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"padding:18px 28px 12px;background:#F1F5F9;border-top:1px solid #E2E8F0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:11px;color:#475569;line-height:1.5;\">\n    <strong>Uganda POE Sentinel</strong> · OVERDUE · ESCALATED · RTSL 14 early-response framework + WHO AFRO IDSR 2021.<br>\n    Alert <strong>DEMO_183022</strong> · fired 30 minutes ago at 2026-04-21 18:00.<br>\n    Open in console → <a href=\"http://localhost/#/active-alerts\" style=\"color:#1D4ED8;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;\">http://localhost/#/active-alerts</a>\n  </p>\n</td></tr></table></td></tr></table></body></html>', 'ALERT', 21, 'UG', 'KYOTERA', 'MUTUKULA', 'SENT', NULL, 0, '2026-04-21 18:31:23', NULL, NULL, 'CMD:demo-all', '2026-04-21 18:31:23', '2026-04-21 18:31:23'),
(258, 118, 'vexa256@gmail.com', NULL, 'EMAIL', 'RESPONDER_INFO_REQUEST', '◈ Info request · DEMO_183022 · Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · please respond 24h', '\n  EXTERNAL RESPONDER · INFO REQUEST\n  The POE needs a direct answer from you before proceeding.\n  ◈ Information requested · DEMO_183022\n  You have been routed as a responder on this case.\n\n\n\n  You are receiving this because a POE Sentinel case has routed a query to your inbox. The case summary and the specific question(s) follow. Reply to this email with the information requested — your response is logged into the case file automatically.\n\n\n\n  What we need to know\n  \n    \n      Has this travell', '<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><meta charset=\"utf-8\"><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\"></head><body style=\"margin:0;padding:0;background:#EEF2F7;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;color:#0F172A;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background:#EEF2F7;padding:24px 12px;\"><tr><td align=\"center\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"640\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"max-width:640px;background:#FFFFFF;border-radius:10px;overflow:hidden;box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><tr><td style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,#B45309 0%,#D97706 60%,#FBBF24 100%);padding:24px 28px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#FEF3C7;font-weight:700;\">EXTERNAL RESPONDER · INFO REQUEST</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:6px;font-size:12px;color:#FEF9C3;\">The POE needs a direct answer from you before proceeding.</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:12px;font-size:22px;font-weight:800;color:#FFFFFF;line-height:1.2;\">◈ Information requested · DEMO_183022</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;font-size:13px;color:#FEF3C7;\">You have been routed as a responder on this case.</div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:22px 28px 0;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">You are receiving this because a POE Sentinel case has routed a query to your inbox. The case summary and the specific question(s) follow. Reply to this email with the information requested — your response is logged into the case file automatically.</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:16px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B45309;font-weight:800;\">What we need to know</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#FFFBEB;border:1px solid #FDE68A;border-radius:6px;\">\n    <ul style=\"margin:0;padding-left:18px;font-size:13px;color:#0F172A;\">\n      <li style=\"margin:4px 0;\">Has this traveller been seen in your facility / district / network before?</li>\n      <li style=\"margin:4px 0;\">Is the case consistent with anything you are currently investigating?</li>\n      <li style=\"margin:4px 0;\">Any outbreak / cluster context you can share?</li>\n      <li style=\"margin:4px 0;\">Can you confirm that contacts listed below can be reached?</li>\n      <li style=\"margin:4px 0;\">Any specific clinical observation, lab result, or epi detail to add?</li>\n    </ul>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B45309;font-weight:800;\">Case at a glance</div>\n  <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin-top:8px;border:1px solid #E2E8F0;border-radius:6px;background:#F8FAFC;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Alert</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">DEMO_183022</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Disease</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) · IHR Annex 2 — Epidemic-Prone (VHF)</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Risk</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;font-weight:700;\">CRITICAL — life-threatening</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Country · POE · district</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">Uganda · MUTUKULA · KYOTERA</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Traveller</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">A. O. · 34 y · FEMALE · Uganda</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Destination in country</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">KAMPALA · Mulago National Referral Hospital, Kampala</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#475569;\">Syndrome · disposition</td><td style=\"padding:6px 12px;font-size:12px;text-align:right;\">VIRAL_HAEMORRHAGIC_FEVER · ISOLATED</td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 28px 0;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B45309;font-weight:800;\">Disease context (for your situational awareness)</div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:8px;padding:12px 14px;background:#FFFBEB;border:1px solid #FDE68A;border-radius:6px;font-size:12px;color:#0F172A;\">\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;\"><strong>CFR:</strong> 50.0% · <strong>Incubation:</strong> 2–21 days (typically 4–10).</p>\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;\"><strong>Transmission:</strong> Direct contact with body fluids of symptomatic case or contaminated fomites; sexual transmission from survivors; bat reservoir.</p>\n    <p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;\"><strong>Isolation posture:</strong> Dedicated VHF isolation ward / treatment centre with buddy-system PPE donning/doffing.</p>\n    <p style=\"margin:0;\"><strong>Differential:</strong> Marburg, Lassa, CCHF, severe malaria, typhoid, meningococcaemia, severe dengue.</p>\n  </div>\n</td>